description:
KPP have partnered with an ASX Listed Australian Institution who are searching for their next Data Insights Specialist to join their Sydney based team.




A unique opportunity to work for one of Australia’s most recognised names. The successful candidate will part of a team who drive impactful change through data driven insights across the business with an aggressive process improvement strategy & high growth corporate agenda with Analytics, & Emerging technology at the centre of it all!




Key Responsibilities:




 * The chosen candidate will be a collaborator between data and the business, to make the insights into actionable outcomes and strive for continuous improvement for the Risk domain using advanced analytics tools and techniques.
 * To be the insights SME! This team pride themselves on being a helpful & highly valued luxury within the business who portfolio leaders see the advantage & benefit gained from working closely with to form critical business decisions.
 * You’ll get stuck into developing critical forecasting models and implementing predictive analytics for the strategic initiatives of your business lines whilst always being a trusted advisor throughout.
 * As well as being on top of data integrity by actioning data validation & cleansing, you will transform your data & insights into engaging & thought-provoking presentations & dashboards all to build the bridge between data & corporate strategy.




Key Requirements:




 * A passion for data, analytics and problem solving!
 * Experience using visualisation tools such as Tableau
 * Experience with Python or SQL is highly desirable.
 * You must be confident and refined in your presentation skills & be able to convey complex data & analytical information to stakeholders.
 * We want those with high business acumen & the ability to make data into actionable outcomes.
 * Must share the same positive, growth mindset attitude & be driven by change!




For more information, please apply!

title: Data Insights Analyst (Risk)

description:
Why join us?



  Do work that matters. We’re pioneering AI software that will help diagnose medical images and raise the standard of healthcare for millions of people every day. 

  Well-funded and global. Annalise.ai has a global presence across APAC, EU and US regions. We’re powered by Harrison.ai (raised Australia’s largest Series B of $129m in 2021).

 Work with a bunch of awesome, genuine people who are passionate about what they do.

  Flexible and remote-friendly working.

 Make an impact. You won’t be another ‘cog in the wheel’ here. We give full trust and autonomy for you to be heard, to work on big & complex projects – and to make a real difference.  

 Grow your career with us. We’re big believers in lifelong learning. You’ll be given a $1000 personal L&D budget, access to LinkedIn Learning, plus opportunities for internal mobility and leadership training to fast-track your career. 

  Generous parental support including 16 weeks gender-neutral paid parental leave and $10,000 support for egg or sperm freezing.  




About Your Role



As a Data Analyst at Annalise.ai/Harrison.ai, you’ll be at the forefront of our data-driven decision-making process. Your insights will directly shape our product development and enhance customer experiences, making you a key player in our mission to scale global healthcare capacity using AI automation.

 

Reporting to the Director of Analytics, you will work within a small team of data and analytics professionals, utilising your strong analytical skills and interpersonal abilities to generate data-driven insights for internal and external stakeholders across customer, commercial, and product domains.

 

The ideal candidate will possess a strong analytical mindset coupled with exceptional interpersonal skills. Proficiency in data analysis tools and techniques is essential, along with the ability to translate findings into actionable insights.






What You'll Do:
 * Generate actionable insights to support decision-making across the organisation,
 * Investigate and troubleshoot issues at customer deployments,
 * Develop and maintain regular reports and dashboards for key stakeholders,
 * Assist in the collection, cleaning, and organisation of data from various sources, and
 * Present findings and recommendations to technical and non-technical audiences
   




What You Bring:
 * Bachelor’s degree in data science, statistics, mathematics, computer science, information systems, economics, engineering, or a related quantitative field,
 * Proven experience in data analysis and visualisation e.g. Tableau, Power BI or similar,
 * Proficiency coding in either SQL, Python or R for data manipulation and analysis,
 * Strong problem-solving skills and attention to detail, and
 * Excellent communication skills, both written and verbal
   




Nice To Haves:
 * Previous experience working in a medical device environment or other highly regulated field, and
 * Previous experience working with data from a health domain
   







What we’re about 

We're problem solvers, redefining what’s possible in medical imaging through AI Technology. Our mission is to raise the standard of healthcare for millions of patients every day.



Yes, we’re a technology company and yes, we’re leveraging the latest AI technologies, but people are at the heart of everything we do. 



Annalise.ai was formed in early 2019, powered by Harrison.ai. Since then, we’ve scaled rapidly and we’re focused on creating AI solutions that help radiologists diagnose medical images.



Our first product, the world's most comprehensive AI clinical decision-support solution for chest x-rays, is already in made available to 1 in 4 radiologists in Australia and rolling out to hundreds more, globally. This solution is capable of detecting 124 findings and was recently featured in a peer-reviewed publication, Lancet Digital Health journal. 



And we’re just getting started.  



Help us shape the future of AI in medical imaging. And most importantly, help us make a real difference in people’s lives.   



What’s next?

If you’re inspired by what we're up to, please apply now and we'll be in touch soon.



We are proud to be an Equal Opportunity Employer. Diversity’s not a buzzword here, it’s in our DNA. Diverse perspectives shape our culture and make our work better. That’s why we’re committed to building inclusive teams that represent a variety of backgrounds and skills. If you need any reasonable adjustments, accessibility assistance or would like to note which pronouns you use at any stage of our hiring process, just contact us at accommodations: people@annalise.ai. We look forward to hearing from you.

description:
Job Title: Data Analyst




About Us

We’re an ambitious start-up that thrives on innovation and energy. Our mission is to deliver cutting-edge data solutions with a focus on ESG (Environmental, Social, Governance). We’re looking for a versatile Data Specialist who’s ready to dive into a fast-paced environment, take on diverse challenges, and make a real impact.




Key Responsibilities

 * Build insightful dashboards and reports using Power BI or AWS Quicksight.
 * Work with AWS tools to manage and analyze large datasets.
 * Collaborate across teams to deliver end-to-end data solutions tailored to client needs.
 * Contribute to ESG-focused data projects, aligning insights with client goals.




Essential Skills

 * Strong proficiency in SQL and Python, with 2-3 years of experience.
 * Experience in data visualization tools like Power BI or AWS Quicksight.




Nice-to-Haves

 * Experience working in a start-up environment or similarly fast-paced roles.
 * An understanding or interest in ESG principles and data-driven sustainability.




What We’re Looking For

 * Adaptability: Someone who’s eager to tackle a wide variety of tasks and projects.
 * Energy and Enthusiasm: Start-up life can be fast and unpredictable. A high-energy attitude and a willingness to jump in are essential.
 * Genuine Passion: We want people who care deeply about data, problem-solving, and sustainability.
 * Collaborative Mindset: You thrive in team environments and enjoy building solutions together.
 * Pragmatic Problem-Solver: You focus on practical, actionable solutions, not just theory or concepts.




Why Join Us?

 * Be part of a growing start-up where your ideas and contributions have a direct impact.
 * Collaborate with a passionate team focused on ESG and sustainability.
 * Enjoy a flexible, dynamic work environment (we don’t work weekends, but things can get busy!).

About The NDIS Quality And Safeguards Commission

The NDIS Quality and Safeguards Commission (the NDIS Commission) is an independent agency established on 1 July to improve the quality and safety of NDIS supports and services. The NDIS Commission is the dedicated national regulator of NDIS service providers in Australia and a non-corporate entity under the Public Governance, Performance and Accountability Act .

Reporting and Insights Team

The Reporting and Insights Team is responsible for the delivery of high-quality data products that underpin data-driven decision-making and enable the NDIS Commission to ensure people with disability receive quality and safe supports and services under the NDIS. The team is accountable for providing business intelligence to operational units, reporting on key metrics and trends, and developing models to enhance Commission data.

description:
At WT, we empower our clients to grow, inspiring confidence through our independent cost management and advisory services. Operating for 75 years, our expertise spans the building, construction, and infrastructure sectors.



We support our clients with an award-winning team of specialists in portfolio and program advisory, quantity surveying and cost management, commercial and financial advisory, carbon and sustainability, and asset and facilities management.



With a global footprint covering Australia, New Zealand, Asia, India, Middle East, North America, Africa, the UK and Europe, our clients can tap into the collective thinking of over 2,000 of the best people in the industry, operating from over 70 offices.





Job Description



We are seeking a Data Analyst for our dynamic Digitals team, you will tackle sophisticated Big Data challenges, crafting analytical solutions that address complex problems for our clients. You are an expert in Power BI and your role involves leveraging your extensive knowledge in data engineering, statistics, and mathematical tools to deliver actionable insights and solutions that meet our clients' specific needs. Collaborating closely with Business Analysts and Software Engineers, you will play a pivotal role in steering projects towards their strategic objectives.



Core responsibilities:



Data Analysis and Solution Development:



 * Develop and implement advanced analytical solutions to complex data-driven problems, ensuring high-end results for our clients, specifically in the Microsoft Power Platform and MS Azure.
 * Utilize statistical methods and data analytics approaches to extract insights and inform decision-making.
 * Design, develop, deploy and maintain client facing products based on MS Power BI and SharePoint.

Collaborative Project Execution:



 * Work in tandem with Business Analysts and Software Engineers to devise and execute optimal strategies for client projects.
 * Participate in cross-functional teams to ensure the integration of analytical solutions with broader project goals.

Technical Proficiency and Innovation:



 * Proficient in Power BI.
 * Demonstrate expertise in various ETL techniques and frameworks, both on-premises and cloud-based (particularly Azure), specifically within Power BI
 * Maintain proficiency in Python, JavaScript, SQL, and other data visualization tools.

Communication and Reporting:



 * Effectively communicate complex analytical concepts and findings to both technical and non-technical stakeholders.
 * Prepare clear, comprehensive reports and presentations that articulate the value and impact of analytical solutions.
   
   

Qualifications


 * Bachelor's degree or higher in computer science, data analytics, data science, data engineering, statistics or related field
 * Proficiency in Power BI and/or Power Platform.
 * Proficiency in Python, JavaScript, SQL,
 * Experience with MS Sharepoint
 * 2-5 years solid experience in creating mathematical and analytical solutions to data-driven problems.
 * Strong background in various ETL techniques and frameworks.
 * Experience with Azure or similar cloud-based solutions.
 * Deep understanding of data processing, data ingestion, and statistical analysis.
 * Excellent communication and interpersonal skills, able to articulate complex data concepts in a clear and accessible manner.
 * Energetic and passionate about advancing technology standards in the field of data analysis.
   
   

Additional Information



At WT, in addition to your competitive salary we offer many perks including:



 * Bi-annual bonus scheme
 * Paid professional memberships
 * Wellbeing days- time to focus on your wellbeing and the community
 * WT’s balanced way of working
 * When you're working from the office, you'll be in an award-winning office fit-out which supports flexible and activity based working in a prime location with amazing views

If you're keen to begin your career with an international cost consultancy at the forefront of Australia's major construction across all sectors: commercial, retail, residential, mixed-use, infrastructure and health, apply now.



Please note: candidates must have full Australian working rights and be located in Melbourne

description:
A Mid- level Data Science role with a best-in-class Aussie organisation.




Our client is looking for a skilled Mid- level Data Scientist to join their team and work on developing logic models and data analysis to help them accurately forecast demand of products and the sustainability of them.




You will bring expertise and knowledge of a variety of technology, best practise and agile methodologies, to build data science solutions. Your role will be collaborative, interacting with other technical squads and business-facing stakeholders in order to deliver technical solutions.







Who You’re Joining:






You will be joining a high-performing data science team based in Brisbane, you will be working end-to-end on a variety of models and analytical products. You will have the opportunity to work with senior stakeholders across the business and collaborate with cross-functional technical teams.




What You’ll Do:




 * Solve complex data problems, building logic models and performing data analysis.
 * Write code with Python and analyse the data.

description:
Company Description

This is an opportunity to join the Octopus Australia team in our Melbourne office. The successful applicant will be able to join the Octopus Australia team on their mission to accelerate Australia's transition to a future powered by renewable energy.

We’re looking for a Business Data Analyst to work within Business Intelligence unit of the Strategic Finance team at Octopus Australia. This role will build, operate, and maintain the information platform which will underpin information flows of Octopus Australia.

The individual in this position will collaborate across the wider Octopus business to understand how data is used and can enhance operations. They will then interpret these needs into functional specifications and play a role in the execution of technical solutions.

About Octopus Group

Octopus Group is a group of entrepreneurial companies on a mission to invest in the ideas, industries and people that will change the world. We are entrepreneurs and investors, applying our expertise and our clients’ money to build a brighter world for future generations. Octopus Group is one of the largest owners of renewable energy projects in Europe and Australia, owning some 260 assets, on behalf of wholesale and institutional investors.

Octopus Australia

Octopus Australia is a renewable energy fund manager and developer harnessing capital and expertise to accelerate the energy transition, with an operating and development portfolio of over $11bn across wind, solar and battery storage. Octopus Australia is more than just an investment manager, we take a data and technology driven approach to constructing an energy portfolio designed for Australia's clean energy future.

Our team of over 50 highly skilled professionals across Melbourne and Sydney, have a unique blend of skills and expertise covering all facets of the renewable energy industry. This allows us to manage projects across their entire lifecycle and create an integrated portfolio of renewable energy and storage assets.

Job Description


 * Database
    * Assist with the continued development and scaling of Octopus Australia’s single source of truth for operational and financial data.
    * Map and document current processes within the organisation and the future state of such systems and processes.
    * Identify optimisation opportunities, ensuring data integrity, security, and governance.
    * Analyse information gathered from multiple sources, reconcile conflicting data, break down complex information into finer details, abstract up from low-level information to a general understanding.
      

 * Insights and Visualisations
    * Implement best practices for data visualization and reporting in Power Bi.
    * Derive actionable insights based on qualitative and quantitative data.
    * Update and where possible automate maintenance of the information platform with monthly and quarterly updates from the business.
    * Develop, maintain, and enhance end-user reports utilising Power BI to facilitate data driven decision making.
      

 * Project Management
    * Collaborate with cross-functional teams to understand business requirements and translate them into technical solutions.
    * Evaluate potential software solutions, including off-the-shelf and open-source components, and the system architecture to ensure that they meet business requirements.
      

 * Finance Experience
    * Conduct thorough data analysis to identify trends, business insights and opportunities for improvement.
    * Assist with responding to Investor requests.
    * Ad-hoc requests from Strategic Finance team.
      
      
      

Qualifications

Ideally, you will have the following qualifications, skills and experiences:


 * Business Data Analyst with over three years of experience, specializing in the development and maintenance of databases, Power BI reports, dashboards, and proficient in data wrangling using programming languages.
 * Experience with source data analysis, data mapping, and identifying source of truth for data across distributed systems/applications.
 * Database: SQL, Python. Visualisation: DAX and Power M, Advanced Excel skills
 * Competence in utilising Azure and other tools within the Power Platform (Power Apps, Power Automate and data flows) would be advantageous.
 * Results oriented problem solver, insights focussed while being tool agnostic.
 * The ability to identify optimisation opportunities, ensuring data security, governance and collaborating with other parts of the business to preserve data integrity.
 * Can manipulate, analyse, and interpret complex data sets with minimal support.
 * High level of attention to detail.
 * A relevant bachelor's degree or higher tertiary qualification in either Business, Data and Analytics or Finance.
   
   
   

Additional Information

What we offer


 *  A competitive salary package including bonus and medical insurance benefits
 * ?? Extra Annual Leave entitlement
 *  Flexible working
 * Ongoing learning and career development opportunities
   
   
   

Octopus has built an exciting and inclusive high-performance culture where employees feel empowered. We also understand the value of diversity, and we are dedicated to creating an inclusive workplace environment. We would welcome people of all backgrounds to apply.

Our Values

At Octopus we don’t just focus on what we do but also how we do it. Our culture is critical to our success and is built around three principles that underpin how we pursue our goals:


 * Be Bold – We like people who make decisions quickly and are OK changing their mind if it turns out there’s a better way of doing things.
 * Be Helpful – We like People who behave like it always day one and who remember without our customers there is no business.
 * Be Straightforward – We like people who have opinions and express them in a way that’s respectful and easy to understand.

description:
Overview

Our large commercial client is looking to engage an a skilled Data Analyst with recent experience in the education field to join a dynamic team on an initial 3-month contract, with the potential for long-term involvement in a multi-year program.

In this role, you’ll analyze existing data, collaborate with stakeholders, and present actionable insights to enhance system, school, and student performance. If you’re ready to leverage your analytical skills to make a difference in education, this role is for you.

Responsibilities

 * Review and analyze existing data sources to identify challenges and opportunities in educational outcomes.
 * Generate evidence-based reports that enhance school and student performance.
 * Collaborate with team members to uncover key findings and develop insights that drive improvements.
 * Present findings and recommendations to senior leaders and facilitate stakeholder discussions.
 * Contribute to creating business cases that outline measurable benefits and resource requirements.
 * Support team initiatives and foster a culture of innovation through data-driven insights.

Skills

 * Strong analytical and statistical skills, with the ability to manage and interpret large datasets with precision.
 * Recent experience in the education sector, with an understanding of educational metrics (e.g., NAPLAN, PAT) and school operations.
 * Expertise in business and financial analysis, with problem-solving skills to address sector-specific challenges.
 * Exceptional communication skills to convey complex findings to diverse stakeholders effectively.
 * Proficiency in Power BI or similar data visualization tools.
 * Ability to obtain a Blue Card and complete a National Criminal Check.

Contact details

For a confidential discussion about the role, contact alana@exclaim-it.com.au

description:
Data Analyst




Overview:

Join a leading global technology company recognized for its commitment to innovation, excellence, and employee well-being. With a proven track record as one of the best workplaces globally, we empower our teams to thrive and achieve their full potential. We are looking for a Senior Business Data Analyst to join our dynamic team in Sydney, Australia.




Responsibilities:

 * Data Analysis & Insights: Extract, process, and analyze complex datasets using tools such as SQL, Python, PySpark, and Pandas. Transform data into actionable insights that drive business decisions.
 * Pipeline Development: Design, build, and maintain efficient data pipelines with technologies like Apache Hadoop, Delta Lake, Hive, Spark, and Databricks.
 * Visualization & Reporting: Create impactful dashboards and reports using visualization tools like Qlik Sense, Tableau, or Google Sheets to communicate findings effectively.
 * Customer Behavior Analysis: Use data to uncover trends, understand customer behavior, and provide insights that align with business goals.
 * Stakeholder Communication: Present complex data insights clearly to stakeholders, including senior executives, ensuring alignment with business objectives.
 * Collaboration & Innovation: Partner with cross-functional teams to fulfill analytics requests and identify opportunities for process improvements and innovative solutions.




Must-Have Skills & Experience:

 * 6+ years in analytics, including at least 1-2 years in a leadership role.
 * Advanced SQL skills with the ability to write and optimize complex queries.
 * Proven expertise in analyzing and integrating large, diverse datasets.
 * Proficiency in data visualization tools such as Qlik Sense or Tableau.
 * Exceptional written and verbal communication skills, including executive-level presentations.
 * Strong multitasking and organizational abilities in a fast-paced environment.




Desirable Skills:

 * Experience with tools like Apache Hadoop, Delta Lake, Hive, Spark, or Databricks.
 * Advanced Python capabilities, including API integrations.
 * Familiarity with statistical modeling and machine learning techniques.
 * Experience in Salesforce and SaaS-based environments.




Benefits:

 * Be part of a company that genuinely values its employees and fosters a supportive, inclusive culture.
 * Work with passionate, innovative professionals committed to making a difference.
 * Access opportunities for professional growth and skill enhancement.
 * Enjoy the perks of a rewarding career in a global organization.

description:
InfoCentric is one of the largest Australian owned specialist Cloud, Data and
Analytics Consulting firms. At InfoCentric, we deliver leading solutions in Data
Strategy and Advisory, Cloud Data Platforms, and Business Analytics and
Insights to Australia’s largest organisations.

We're hiring for a Graduate Consultant to join our team, working in a Data Analytics and Data Engineering role, based out of Ballarat. Working along side a small team of experience InfoCentric consultants, you'll be learning what it's like to work in industry, working on real client projects to deliver quality solutions.

This is a graduate level role. We're looking for people who can:

 * demonstrate the knowledge gained through their studies
 * are keen to learn and upskills
 * keen to work as part of a team



We're looking for someone based in Ballarat or happy to work 1 day a week from a Ballarat office for the first 12 months, with the intention to move work location to the Melbourne CBD.



About You:

 * Graduated from a Information Technology, Information Systems or similar degree by November 2024
 * Available to work full time
 * Keen to learn and upskill, with an interest in Data Analytics and/or Engineering
 * Have studied or has experience with Python and SQL
 * Have studied or has experience with a reporting platform like Power BI or Tableau
 * Have great written and verbal communication skills



About the Role:

 * Work in a supportive team of Technical Consultants to learn new tools and technologies
 * Have a career plan built around you, to meet your interests and career goals
 * Gain hands on experience delivery work for one of our enterprise customers
 * Build reports and dashboards based on client needs
 * Provide support for their data platform (including working with stakeholders from the client)
 * Involved building ETL and Ingestion Pipelines, using Python, SQL and Azure



About Us:

We really believe that our employees shape our business and are at the core of our success. We have had many employees start their careers with us and grow into positions of responsibility. 

Our core values below really describe what is important to us as individuals and as a team.



Realise Opportunity

 * We'll pay for your training and certifications, including the latest technologies from AWS, Azure, and Snowflake
 * You'll gain mentorship and collaboration from industry leaders
 * You'll gain experience in complex client projects from the graduate level

Thrive Together & Embrace Diversity

 * Receive genuine recognition for work and valued behaviour.
 * Regular social events to connect with each other. Previous events include private cinema screenings, bubble soccer, minigolf, bowling, and social drinks.
 * Be part of embracing and celebrating team diversity

Think Big Picture

 * Work flexibly to balance family, life, and career
 * Create impact and positive change for the team and business

description:
About Us




Santos provides reliable, affordable energy for progress and seeks to provide lower carbon energy over time.




Santos is a global energy company with operations across Australia, Papua New Guinea, Timor-Leste and the United States.




At Santos, our goal is to be a global leader in the energy evolution to low-carbon fuels that help the world decarbonise and continue to provide the reliable, affordable energy the world needs for modern life and human progress.




Santos is an important Australian domestic gas supplier and LNG supplier in Asia. We are committed to supplying critical fuels such as oil and gas, and abating emissions through carbon capture and storage, energy efficiency projects, use of renewables in our operations and high-quality offsets. Santos will also seek to develop low-carbon fuels as customer demand evolves.




For 70 years, Santos has been working in partnership with local communities, providing jobs and business opportunities, safely developing natural gas resources and from there powering industries and households.




Santos seeks to deliver long-term value to shareholders through our diverse portfolio of high-quality, long-life, low-cost oil and gas assets, carbon storage resources and infrastructure.




The Santos portfolio is value accretive and resilient across a range of decarbonisation scenarios. Santos has a climate transition action plan that will continue to evolve for the global energy evolution.




Santos has a regional operating model with a strong local focus. The Company’s operating structure comprises three regional business units focused on enabling and executing corporate strategy. Two divisions – Santos Energy Solutions and Santos Upstream Gas and Liquids – are accountable for global portfolio management and strategy.




About the Role






Are you passionate about leveraging and managing data to drive decisions in the oil and gas industry?






Santos is looking for a Data Analyst to join the Subsurface Data Services team to enhance the delivery and quality of Subsurface (Geological, Geophysical & Engineering) Data for the Eastern Australia and PNG Division.






This role is vital to ensuring high-quality and readily available subsurface data for asset teams, regulatory and government compliance and supporting senior members of the team with data improvement initiatives and projects, collaborating with function staff, acting as the asset representative when required.






Key accountabilities include:




 * Data Delivery: Provide sourcing, validating, ingesting, curating, and presenting subsurface data in compliance with company standards and processes.
 * Data Management: Maintain master data stores for subsurface data and advocate for process improvement opportunities in data management.
 * Documentation: Prepare and maintain documentation for essential subsurface data administration tasks and workflows.
 * Data Quality Improvement: Enhance the quality of existing data by undertaking data management project work and data analysis as prescribed by the Asset and/or Function.
 * Data Distribution & Regulatory Compliance: Prepare and distribute data to joint venture parties, external vendors, and regulators (DEM, GSQ, etc.) as required.






About You




To stand out in this role, we are looking for analytical, collaborative individuals with demonstrated skills and experience in:

 * Ideally have experience in oil and gas exploration and production, gained at a major oil and gas company or application vendor, but not essential
 * Sound knowledge in data management and data analysis.
 * Ideally have SQL and Python scripting skills and demonstrated proficiency in using databases, document management systems and dashboarding tools.
 * Proven experience in supporting or managing projects.
 * Proficiency with Microsoft Office applications, including Excel, Word, PowerPoint; and Microsoft Power Apps and other data and workflow automation tools is highly desirable.






Supporting a Diverse Workforce




Santos acknowledges that we operate on the traditional lands of Aboriginal people. We recognise the traditional rights to maintain the culture, identities, traditions, and customs on their country. We are committed to an inclusive environment where people feel comfortable to be themselves. We want our people to feel that all voices are heard, all cultures respected and that a variety of perspectives are not only welcome – they are essential to our ongoing success.



We treat each other fairly and with dignity regardless of race, gender, nationality, ethnic origin, religion, age, sexual orientation, or anything else that makes us different.




Australian Aboriginal and / or Torres Strait Islander jobseekers are strongly encouraged to apply.




How to Apply




Applications must be submitted via the online recruitment system before COB 5th August 2024.






A requirement of this role is that you will need to have in place the legal work rights for Australia to apply.






Potential Scams




There are a number of fake adverts that are impersonating Santos Limited, in these instances you will receive an e-mail from a generic e-mail address. We do not make offers without interviews or due diligence taking place. You will know if an advert is genuine if you are directed to the Santos company careers page to apply which is https://recruitment.santos.com/

For more info, here's our hiring video: Open here!

Responsibilities:


 * Sourcing, processing, analyzing, and interpreting large & complex datasets within our growing forecast offering.
 * Developing our power market and dispatch models to grow and enhance Modo's product offering. We use Python and the standard scientific computing stack (Numpy, Pandas, SciPy, ScikitLearn, etc.).
 * Working closely with our product and analytics functions to ensure the product we deliver aligns closely with user needs and provides value to the wider Modo team.
   
   

Qualifications:


 * 3 to 5 years experience using Python (or another programming language e.g. R, C++, Java) and with the scientific computing stack (Numpy, Pandas, SciPy, ScikitLearn, etc.).
 * Strong quantitative skills and a proven track record of solving complex technical problems using data analysis, machine learning, and optimization techniques.
 * Hands-on experience with cloud environments (e.g., AWS) for deploying data science models.
 * Proven experience with optimisation using linear programming with a preference for Python-based implementations.
 * Proven ability to produce data science models and insights that are directly delivered to external customers, with a track record of handling high-visibility, customer-facing outputs.
 * Previous experience in energy modeling, with a specific focus on the Australian power systems.
 * Excellent technical communication skills, with the ability to explain complex data science concepts to non-technical stakeholders.
 * A self-starter attitude, with an eagerness to dive headfirst into problems and pick things up quickly.
 * Nice to have:
    * A degree in a quantitative field such as mathematics, engineering, computer science, physics or a related discipline.
      

Important Details:


 * We work in a Hybrid Environment: You split your time between working from home and working in our Sydney office (Tuesday through Thursday).
   
   

Modo Energy is an equal-opportunity employer. Our employment decisions are made on the basis of qualifications, merit, and business need. We do not discriminate against age, national origin, physical or mental disability, race, religion, pregnancy, sexual orientation, gender identity, veteran status, or any other characteristic protected by federal, state, or local law. If you need assistance or a reasonable accommodation with an application or the interview process please contact us via email at careers@modo.energy.

What you can expect from Modo

We want to attract and retain the best talent at Modo, and we give our people the freedom and opportunity to develop themselves and flourish.

We are committed to building a diverse and inclusive team at Modo, as we believe a variety of backgrounds, skills and interests is what makes our company stronger. If you share our values and our enthusiasm for supporting the transition to greener energy systems, we encourage you to apply. We have a number of positions open which could be for a range of backgrounds and experience levels. description:
Hi, we’re PEXA

Every time a house is bought, sold or refinanced in Australia your lawyer, conveyancer and lender will most likely use a digital platform to settle your property, this is where we come in. PEXA’s world-first digital settlement platform has revolutionised the way we exchange property in Australia helping over 20,000 people a week safely settle their homes. And this is just the beginning. Our data and insights are helping organisations unlock the intel they need to drive change and possibilities.

Since starting our journey in 2010, we now employ a team of over 1,000 people working across multiple continents. We’re still growing, innovating and looking ahead, but behind our greatest achievements, there is a team of curious creators and big thinkers. That’s why, we’re looking for ambitious people like yourself to join the team.

About The Role

As a member of the Climate Resilience Solutions team, you will play a pivotal role in researching climate change at global, regional, and local levels. You'll collaborate closely with stakeholders to gather, analyse, and interpret data from various sources, including the atmosphere, oceans, and land. Your work will contribute to the development of climate data products, computer models, and analytical frameworks that support informed decision-making and drive climate resilience across industries.

Key Accountabilities


 * Conduct research on climate change impacts and adaptation strategies.
 * Collect, manage, and analyse geospatial data related to environmental risks and natural hazards.
 * Develop and maintain standards, policies, and quality assurance protocols for climate data products.
 * Build and validate computer models to simulate climate change scenarios and natural hazard events.
 * Conduct spatial analysis to identify potential impacts and hazards, and provide recommendations for risk mitigation strategies.
 * Stay informed about legislative and regulatory frameworks related to climate resilience and disclosures.
   
   

Skills And Experience


 * Experience with Python programming or other similar programming language.
 * Experience in developing models related to natural catastrophes and analysing climate-related risks.
 * Understanding of climate change concepts and risk assessment methodologies.
 * Experience working with climate data, geospatial data, and large-scale numerical models.
 * Proficiency in data management, quality assurance, and statistical analysis.
 * Relevant qualifications in environmental engineering, statistics, climate science, or related fields.
 * Excellent analytical skills and a track record of driving climate resilience outcomes.
   
   

A career at PEXA starts with you!

If you think you have the required skills, an appetite to learn and would be a great fit, we’d love to hear from you – even if you don’t tick all the boxes. At PEXA we support your growth and help you discover your full potential.

Why join us


 * Flexibility is in our DNA
 * Your holistic wellbeing is important to us. Enjoy meditation, yoga, boxing classes?and a wellness day each month to recharge!
 * We know that work is just one aspect of your life. That’s why we offer up to 12 weeks ‘workcation’ for you to extend personal travel time and work remotely
 * Take the opportunity to purchase up to four weeks additional annual leave per year
 * Learn from the best and upskill with PEXA Academy certifications and grow your career
   
   

Our commitment to our people and a better future

At PEXA we want you to embrace your best self each day, creating an environment where everyone can contribute and participate, so that every person can reach their full potential. We want our people to feel equally valued, supported and celebrated. With market-leading benefits that make a difference, we’re committed to supporting individuals, families and carers. Your culture, gender, sexual orientation, language and other attributes make you unique! We couldn't be prouder to have a team that reflects the richness of our wider community.

We’re a proud ‘Circle Back Initiative’ Employer and commit to responding to every applicant.

Stay Connected

A career at PEXA is exciting, challenging and rewarding, and we’re always on the lookout for talented individuals to join the team. You can learn more about life at PEXA on our website and social channels too.

Job Description

Data Analyst | 55403


 * Permanent
 * Gold Coast Location
 * Part of multi-billion-dollar UNITE program
   
   

How will I help?

As a Data Analyst, you will be responsible for producing data analytics and insights. You will also support the performance of key controls to meet regulatory requirements and/ or mitigate risks.

Key responsibilities include:


 * Extract, manipulate and analyse data using SAS and SQL
 * Internal and external stakeholder management
 * Attend to individual requests for information and/or assistance – requests can vary from small analytical requests to deep dive which involves participation in discussions with stakeholders
 * Interrogate, identify and solve data integrity issues
 * Ensure that all processes, procedures, outcomes and changes are appropriately documented and controlled
 * Proactively communicate and collaborate with team to ensure projects, business-as-usual activities, governance framework and compliance obligations are managed in a coordinated manner
 * Provide recommendations to internal business partners to assist them in achieving objectives
 * Analyse and translate complex information into a form that can be used by the team and its customers for quick and quality decision making
 * Produce, check and deliver data for designated regulatory communications with success measured by accuracy, timeliness as well as meeting all legal, compliance and regulatory requirements
 * Work with business stakeholders to gather Dashboard/reporting requirement
 * Develop and support repeatable and customisable analytics processes for reporting
   
   

What’s in it for me?

You’ll play a significant part of the future of a business that has been around for over 200 years. Our purpose is to create better futures together. So, we’ll back you in the development of your career, internal career prospects, and flexible working. You’ll also keep learning to grow your career, backed by a fantastic team of people with a can-do, supportive structure. Whatever shape your family takes, we offer generous paid and unpaid parental leave for your nominated primary and support carers. This includes leave to organise adoptions, surrogacy, and foster care arrangements. And we continue to pay your super contributions while you take all the time you need to get your new family settled.

What do I need?

We are seeking a highly skilled Analytics professional with over 3 years of experience. The ideal candidate will have a strong background in SQL, Teradata, and Base SAS, with additional expertise in Python, R, and advanced Excel for data extraction and analysis from large customer bases.

The role requires exceptional conceptual, analytical, and problem-solving abilities, along with a keen attention to detail. Strong communication, influencing, and negotiation skills are essential, as is proven stakeholder management experience and the ability to engage effectively at all levels. The successful candidate will be adept at transforming quantitative and qualitative analysis into actionable business insights and solutions.

What’s it like to work there?

We are a collaborative team of passionate people with a shared ambition to make a difference for our customers, our communities and each other. At Westpac, making a difference means creating impact, unlocking our own and each other’s passions, and transformative success stories to create better futures together.

As well as competitive remuneration and a great culture, joining the Westpac family gives you access to a wide range of employee benefits to help you manage your priorities - whether that means family life, work/life balance, ambition to grow or all the little perks in between.

We’ll empower you to shape your career path. Through personalised upskilling, mentoring, and training opportunities, you’re in control of where you start and how you’ll grow.

As an equal opportunity employer, we are proud to have created a culture and work environment that values diversity and flexibility – and champions inclusion.

Hear from some of our people and their experiences working with us.

How do I apply?

Start here. Just click on the APPLY or APPLY NOW button.

At Westpac, we’re all about creating a supportive culture and ensuring our workplaces, branches, products, and services are accessible and inclusive for everyone—our customers, employees, and the wider community. If you’re interested in discussing workplace flexibility, please feel free to mention it in your application.

We invite candidates of all ages, genders, sexual orientation, cultural backgrounds, people with disability, neurodiverse individuals, veterans and reservists, and Indigenous Australians to apply. If you have questions about the recruitment process, please email talentacquisition@westpac.com.au .

Do you need reasonable adjustments during the recruitment process?

About Us

G’day Group is recognised as Australia’s largest regional accommodation provider and a leading tourism organisation in Australia. The business has an enviable portfolio of brands and a truly national footprint that continues to expand, including 85+ owned and operated parks and resorts (Discovery Parks), 220+ licensed independent parks (G’day Parks), 195,000+ Rewards Program members (G’day Rewards) and the #1 travel app in the App Store (WikiCamps).

The Role

As the Business Intelligence Analyst, you will be responsible for analysing and interpreting information from large data sets, providing insights on aggregated data metrics and identifying and communicating past and predicted trends, through dashboards and other tools, for the business to make strategic data-driven decisions.

With a flair of creativity, you will have the opportunity to solve problems, to interact with best-in-breed technology and to communicate key insights in a variety of formats and within a variety of business domains such as customer experience, market operations, finance and HR/employees.

This is an exciting opportunity to be a central part of a vibrant cross-functional team focused on delivering business outcomes by leveraging unique insights brought about through an effective data management capability.

Key responsibilities of the role will include -


 * Perform data extraction, transformation, and loading (ETL) processes
 * Develop and maintain dashboards, reports, and visualisations using Power BI
 * Conduct data quality checks and data validation to ensure accuracy and reliability of data
 * Identify and interpret trends, patterns, and anomalies in data and provide actionable insights and recommendations
 * Communicate and present data findings and solutions to various stakeholders
 * Collaborate with other analysts, developers, and business users to understand data requirements and deliver solutions
   
   

Your Experience

A Bachelor’s Degree or high in Business Analytics, Data Science, Computer Science, Statistics or related field. You will have experience with SQL and at least one programming language such as Python, R or Java. You will have strong analytical skills and a natural skill in problem-solving. You will have experience using Power BI and a knowledge of data warehousing, data modelling and data mining concepts and techniques.

You will have the ability to confidently engage and communicate to both technical and non-technical stakeholders. You will have a natural curiosity and passion for data and above all less a desire to learn new skills. You will possess a high level of energy, self-motivation, autonomy, initiative, and attention to detail to be successful in meeting the business demands at G’day Group. Your naturally upbeat and open style will fit our cultural values. You will have a highly organised mindset with the ability to assess the urgency of work allocated to you by various stakeholders.

title: Data Scientist

description:
Data Scientist

 * Rapidly growing fixed income fund manager
 * Research and coding intensive data science role
 * Competitive compensation including performance-based bonus




Role/Responsibilities

We are a successful fixed-income fund manager running multiple portfolios/strategies looking for a full-time data scientist who is able to apply a range of data science skills to the fixed income market.




Reporting to the lead data scientist as well as portfolio managers, the role is full-time and will span long-term project research and engineering duties. In particular the role will involve: using R and other languages for asset pricing and portfolio management modelling; managing and munging large datasets from multiple sources; benchmarking research methods against state-of-the-art academic literature; back-testing models against suitable benchmarks and metrics; driving model development and research into production grade systems; producing intuitive and immersive data visualisations; producing written method papers that are clear and well-communicated; delivering outputs/results according to pre-agreed timetables; and generally investigating ways in which our technical methods can be enhanced.




Pay will be market competitive in all respects with the opportunity to earn significant bonuses based on performance and equity participation in the business.




Skills/Experience

Ideally suits a reliable quant researcher or data scientist with an advanced degree in stats/engineering/science/actuarial who has applied data science techniques in industry, and wants to make a long-term commitment to their next position. Suitable candidates will possess the following attributes:

 * Team player
 * Excellent statistical modelling skills
 * Excellent data munging and analysis skills.
 * Understanding of good engineering practices when contributing to large shared code bases
 * Excellent communication (written/verbal) skills
 * High-intensity work ethic + willingness to work outside normal hours
 * No prerequisite financial markets knowledge/experience required.




This role uses the R tidyverse framework for data munging. If unfamiliar with tidyverse, then experience with R data.table, Python Pandas, SQL or similar is required together with the willingness to transition to R tidyverse.




Benefits

It is expected a market-competitive contract will be agreed with the opportunity to participate in the bonus pool and equity ownership scheme. The work will be demanding but also highly creative with the right candidate able to assume significant responsibilities and drive innovation.

title: Data Specialist

description:
Job Description

Data Analyst | 55403


 * Permanent
 * Gold Coast Location
 * Part of multi-billion-dollar UNITE program
   
   

How will I help?

As a Data Analyst, you will be responsible for producing data analytics and insights. You will also support the performance of key controls to meet regulatory requirements and/ or mitigate risks.

Key responsibilities include:


 * Extract, manipulate and analyse data using SAS and SQL
 * Internal and external stakeholder management
 * Attend to individual requests for information and/or assistance – requests can vary from small analytical requests to deep dive which involves participation in discussions with stakeholders
 * Interrogate, identify and solve data integrity issues
 * Ensure that all processes, procedures, outcomes and changes are appropriately documented and controlled
 * Proactively communicate and collaborate with team to ensure projects, business-as-usual activities, governance framework and compliance obligations are managed in a coordinated manner
 * Provide recommendations to internal business partners to assist them in achieving objectives
 * Analyse and translate complex information into a form that can be used by the team and its customers for quick and quality decision making
 * Produce, check and deliver data for designated regulatory communications with success measured by accuracy, timeliness as well as meeting all legal, compliance and regulatory requirements
 * Work with business stakeholders to gather Dashboard/reporting requirement
 * Develop and support repeatable and customisable analytics processes for reporting
   
   

What’s in it for me?

You’ll play a significant part of the future of a business that has been around for over 200 years. Our purpose is to create better futures together. So, we’ll back you in the development of your career, internal career prospects, and flexible working. You’ll also keep learning to grow your career, backed by a fantastic team of people with a can-do, supportive structure. Whatever shape your family takes, we offer generous paid and unpaid parental leave for your nominated primary and support carers. This includes leave to organise adoptions, surrogacy, and foster care arrangements. And we continue to pay your super contributions while you take all the time you need to get your new family settled.

What do I need?

We are seeking a highly skilled Analytics professional with over 3 years of experience. The ideal candidate will have a strong background in SQL, Teradata, and Base SAS, with additional expertise in Python, R, and advanced Excel for data extraction and analysis from large customer bases.

The role requires exceptional conceptual, analytical, and problem-solving abilities, along with a keen attention to detail. Strong communication, influencing, and negotiation skills are essential, as is proven stakeholder management experience and the ability to engage effectively at all levels. The successful candidate will be adept at transforming quantitative and qualitative analysis into actionable business insights and solutions.

What’s it like to work there?

We are a collaborative team of passionate people with a shared ambition to make a difference for our customers, our communities and each other. At Westpac, making a difference means creating impact, unlocking our own and each other’s passions, and transformative success stories to create better futures together.

As well as competitive remuneration and a great culture, joining the Westpac family gives you access to a wide range of employee benefits to help you manage your priorities - whether that means family life, work/life balance, ambition to grow or all the little perks in between.

We’ll empower you to shape your career path. Through personalised upskilling, mentoring, and training opportunities, you’re in control of where you start and how you’ll grow.

As an equal opportunity employer, we are proud to have created a culture and work environment that values diversity and flexibility – and champions inclusion.

Hear from some of our people and their experiences working with us.

How do I apply?

Start here. Just click on the APPLY or APPLY NOW button.

At Westpac, we’re all about creating a supportive culture and ensuring our workplaces, branches, products, and services are accessible and inclusive for everyone—our customers, employees, and the wider community. If you’re interested in discussing workplace flexibility, please feel free to mention it in your application.

We invite candidates of all ages, genders, sexual orientation, cultural backgrounds, people with disability, neurodiverse individuals, veterans and reservists, and Indigenous Australians to apply. If you have questions about the recruitment process, please email talentacquisition@westpac.com.au .

Do you need reasonable adjustments during the recruitment process?

We can provide reasonable adjustments for individuals with disability and/or neurodiversity. If you require an adjustment to be made during the recruitment process at any stage, please email talentacquisition@westpac.com.au

* Hybrid working and great work life balance
 * Experience in PowerBI, SQL, R or Python

About Us

At ubank, we want to empower the digital generation to be more successful with money. Think of us more as a daily money companion. One that brings together the ability for customers to see their money in one place, with smart features and real-time insights designed to help them get ahead.

With ubank, our customers can discover what it feels like to save more, see exactly where they’re spending and own their own home faster. In short, we want to help them achieve real momentum with money.

Your why

You are a driven data professional with a passion for using insights to drive smarter decision making and an improved customer experience. But you also aren’t afraid to roll up your sleeves to do some building. You are excited by the opportunity to work with cutting-edge technology and want to play a key role in the transformation of analytics and insights delivery for a rapidly-growing, digitally-native business.

How You Will Spend Your Time

As a Data Analyst you will be expected to:


 * Work with business stakeholders to understand and document their data requirements
 * Explore and profile data and develop analytics use cases
 * Work collaboratively with our Data Engineers to understand underlying data assets and co-build business centric and reusable assets to fulfil analytical needs
 * Perform data quality activities for any newly developed or updated reports, dashboards and outputs, checking for completeness and integrity against established processes
 * Execute analytics work packages from across a range of business units, from strategic ideation through to data build, execution, and measurement
   
   

What Makes You Tick


 * You enjoy working as part of a collaborative, solutions focused team
 * You have strong attention to detail but can still see the big picture
 * You can prioritize, adapt to change quickly and work well with ambiguity
 * You put your hand up for help when stuck
 * You have knowledge in financial process and systems
 * You are curious, open to learn & thrive in a growing business
   
   

What You Will Bring


 * Appropriate industry experience/qualifications in data analytics/insights
 * Ability to take requirements from non-technical business stakeholders and translate these into clear analytics outcomes
 * Experience building datasets to support self-service visualisation tools (Power BI)
 * Extensive experience using relational databases and analytic tools such as SQL, R or Python to extract meaning from complex data
 * A disciplined approach to curating and maintaining business facing data assets with long term usability
   
   

Essential


 * Practical experience and can demonstrable this in the discovery, exploration and analysis of large and complex data sets, preferably including financial services data and banking products
 * Practical knowledge of data preparation, transformation and modelling techniques
 * Experience working with cloud-based analytics platforms

 * Ability to simplify the complex and confidently present insights back to the business
 * Strong problem-solving skills
 * Exposure to the Growth and Marketing space and Marketing Technologies (Martech) that integrate customer data
   
   

Desirable


 * Previous work experience with the Databricks platform (highly desirable)
 * Exposure to Data Vault or other similar data modelling
 * Experience working cross-functionally with data engineering and modelling teams
 * Exposure to the Growth and Marketing space and Marketing Technologies (Martech) that integrate customer data
   
   

Why Ubank?

Hybrid working model - with 3 days in our central Sydney CBD office located above Wynyard station.

Highly collaborative and positive culture

Strong internal development & growth opportunities


 * other fantastic benefits to support!
   
   

Our Values

Delight the Customer - We put the customer’s best interests at the forefront of everything we do. We believe financial success will follow customer success.

Agile and Brave - Constantly collaborating in new ways to create something genuinely innovative.

Value Each Other - We respect everyone’s contribution, embracing a common goal and championing individuality.

Frank and Authentic - A high performing team who say what we mean and mean what we say to create a strong team culture.

Show Up - We bring our passion, positivity, and sense of fun every day to embrace the challenges of changing the banking game

description:
SkyCity Adelaide is currently on the lookout for an experienced Data Insights Analyst to join our Host Responsibility team to support decision making and identify continuous improvement opportunities.

About The Opportunity

This newly created role will be responsible for analysing data related to gambling behaviours, identifying potential issues and trends, and assisting in the development and implementation of responsible gambling initiatives. Working collaboratively with a range of internal stakeholders, this role will enable data-driven decision making to promote responsible gambling practices within SkyCity, and will be accountable for producing monthly, quarterly, and annual reporting to internal stakeholders and external regulators (including Consumer & Business Services).

The role will also assist the wider Host Responsibility team and function with non-customer facing duties that support our overall approach to customer care, such as assisting the VIP loyalty tier upgrade review process.

About You

You will have proven experience in qualitative and quantitative data analysis (preferably in the gambling or gaming industry), coupled with tertiary qualifications in a related field (statistics, data analysis, psychology, gambling studies). You will be highly proficient in Excel and data visualisation tools such as PowerBI and will be an analytical and critical thinker with a high level of integrity that can collaborate and build relationships with key stakeholders around you. You will have an excellent ability to deliver results that are timely, accurate and quality focused, coupled with excellent communication skills. You will also be committed to promoting responsibly gaming and ensuring the well-being of casino patrons.

About Us

Besides working with great people and getting first-hand experience of SkyCity's newest entertainment offerings, you will also be rewarded with a range of employee benefits including;

Be part of a supportive, dynamic team where every day brings something new.


 * The satisfaction of knowing your work makes a real difference to the people of Adelaide.
 * Free employee meals available at our employee restaurant
 * In-house dry-cleaning service, which is also available for personal use at a discounted rate.
 * Subsidised car parking and public transport tickets.

 * Employee reward and recognition programs.

To join our Host Responsibility team as our Data Insights Analyst, please apply online today.

No recruitment agencies please.

At SkyCity, our career opportunities are as diverse as our workforce. We don't just embrace differences; we value and support them. Our hiring is centred on capability and performance, regardless of gender, gender identity, race, origin, age, educational background, disability, or religious beliefs. We're here to empower you to shine. Our willingness to adapt ensures you can chart your path with us! Join us at SkyCity and be extraordinary by being you.
title: Data Insights Analyst

description:
About Us

At ANZ, we're applying new ways technology and data can be harnessed as we work towards a common goal: to improve the financial wellbeing and sustainability of our millions of customers.

About The Role

As a Data Analyst within the Data Portfolio, you’ll play a key role in helping the CRR&A Data initiatives. You will collaborate closely with a team of Data Scientists, Data Engineers, and Data Analysts, as well as business teams within the CRR&A portfolio.

Banking is changing and we’re changing with it, giving our people great opportunities to try new things, learn and grow. Whatever your role at ANZ, you’ll be building your future, while helping to build ours.

Role Type: 6 month opportunity

Role Location: Melbourne

Work Hours: Full time

What will your day look like?

This role will help the CRR&A Data team accelerate the closure of events in the backlog of our risk management system NFR Hub through a program of work designed to provide insights and improve event management processes.

As a member of the Retail Analytics CRR&A Data team, you bring advanced data analysis expertise and a passion for leveraging data to enhance our responses to regulatory requirements.

As a Data Analyst, your key accountabilities will include:


 * Developing management dashboards and the supporting data pipelines that contribute to regulatory reporting.
 * Developing standard Python/SQL queries and procedures to assist with the process optimisation.
 * Automating new and existing procedures and reporting workflows using Python or other scripting languages.
 * Providing data initiative support and expertise to product teams in Aus Retail and business teams within the CRR&A portfolio.
 * Developing insights and progress reporting for stakeholders.
   
   
   

What will you bring?

To grow and be successful in this role, you will ideally bring the following:


 * Recent and extensive experience in a Data Analyst or Data Engineering role.
 * Extensive knowledge and experience with tools and techniques for analysis, data manipulation and presentation (e.g., Python, SQL, Tableau, QlikSense).
 * Analytical and inquisitive mindset to continuously improve the level of insight surfaced.
 * Strong ability to translate data insights into practical business recommendations.
 * Strong data visualisation skills.
 * Ability to effectively communicate to all stakeholders (technical and non-technical).
 * Data engineering tools (e.g., dbt, Spark, Airflow)
 * Experience with Big Data/Cloud platforms and technologies (Hadoop, Kubernetes)
 * Knowledge Management platforms and practices (GitHub, Confluence)
 * Degree qualifications in Data Science, Computer Science, Information Technology, Information Statistics, Applied Mathematics, or equivalent industry experience in data analysis, engineering, or related fields.
   
   
   

You’re not expected to have 100% of these skills. At ANZ a growth mindset is at the heart of our culture, so if you have most of these things in your toolbox, we’d love to hear from you.

So why join us?

From the moment you join ANZ, you'll be doing meaningful work that will shape a world where people and communities thrive.

But it's not just our customers who'll feel your impact. You'll feel it too. Because at ANZ, you'll have the resources, opportunities, and support you need to take the next big step in your career.

We're a diverse bunch at ANZ in different roles, different locations, doing different things. That's why we have a range of flexible working arrangements, so our people can 'make work, work for them'. We also provide a range of benefits including access to health and wellbeing services and discounts on selected products and services from ANZ and more.

At ANZ, you'll be part of an organisation where the different backgrounds, perspectives and life experiences of our people are celebrated. That's because we're committed to building a workplace that reflects the diversity of the communities we serve. We welcome applications from everyone and encourage you to talk to us about any adjustments you may require to our recruitment process or the role itself. If you're a candidate with a disability or access requirement, and have an enquiry about the support provided, please let us know on your application or visit ANZ Accessibility and Inclusion Programs for alternate contact methods.

To find out more about working at ANZ, visit https://www.anz.com.au/careers . You can apply for this role by visiting ANZ Careers and searching for reference number 82306 .

title: Data Analyst (503185)

description:
Our Marketing Data Analysts work with our customers to get their marketing and sales data into our Product, GrowthOS.We've built DataOS to help with this process, so you'll learn that product and become a subject matter expert for our customers. This role is a combination of Customer Success, Marketing Analytics with some project management. You could come from one of those backgrounds or possibly Digital/Media agency strategy or analyst and want to move into the tech & startup world.

When customers with with Mutinex to measure their marketing effectiveness, you'll run the process to get their critical marketing data into our GrowthOS product, leveraging DataOS as the tool for gathering, collecting and ingesting that data. You'll be able to read marketing data and recognise the difference between good and bad marketing data. You can spot problems in datasets and know how to find & extract data from other sources. Working in the Customer team with other Marketing Analysts, you'll manage multiple customer projects at once which will require good organisational skills.




Key Responsibilities:

? Data Integration: Responsible for integrating marketing and sales data into our

GrowthOS product, within the specified timeframes. Ensure adherence to data quality

standards and alignment with business objectives under supervision.

? Learn DataOS: Develop a strong understanding of DataOS. Support senior team

members in guiding customers through the data ingestion process, focusing on clear

and accurate data interpretation and utilisation.

? Data Analysis: Perform analysis of marketing data to distinguish between different

quality datasets. Assist in identifying and resolving data-related issues with the

guidance of senior analysts.

? Collaboration with Teams: Collaborate with the Data Science, Product,

Engineering, and Customer Success teams. Contribute to ensuring integrated efforts

and learn to align these teams towards common goals and customer

experiences. Responsible for internal communications, ensuring effective project

updates using tools like Salesforce, Slack and Jira.

? Project Management: Manage and prioritise multiple customer projects. Develop

organisational skills and learn to handle project demands effectively under the

guidance of senior staff.

? Customer Interaction: Assist in building and maintaining relationships with

customers. Support senior team members in providing strategic recommendations on

datasets, structure, and quality.

? Professional Development: Engage in continuous learning opportunities. Contribute

to personal and professional growth, and the advancement of the team and

organisation.

What we are looking for:

? Around 1 years+ commercial experience in roles that require analysis of

marketing data

? Exploratory data analysis (EDA)

? Good SQL & Python knowledge

? Strong customer facing ability including communication, stakeholder

management & time management

? Highly organised people looking to join an exciting, fast-growing tech start up




ABOUT MUTINEX:

We might be an early stage startup but we already have strong product market fit, household name clients (Samsung, Mars, CUB and ING to name a few) and millions in revenue.

Being early stage means we're also still pretty scrappy and you wouldn't be coming into a well oiled machine, yet. But you would get a lot of opportunity to design, build and oil the machine until it's super oily.

We aren't aiming to be another Tech Unicorn because Unicorns aren't real. We are aiming (and confident of being) more like a real and really big animal that lives for a long time, like a Bowhead Whale.

Mutinex is a startup B2B SaaS platform that provides in-depth data analytics for marketers to better understand their ROI and make better decisions with future spend.

Founded in Australia, we've hit millions in ARR & have (very!) recent funding ($5 million in May 2023 & $9.5 million in October 2023 backed by EVP, and most recently $17.5m) that we'll use for growing our team to continue to improve our product, bring in new customers and enable them to make better and more informed decisions.

We have a hybrid work environment at two days a week in the office (Monday, Friday) with teams in Sydney, Melbourne and New York.

With a team of around 70 people, we value high-quality communication, strong opinions that are held loosely and people who can give and take feedback well.

Equity (ESOP) is offered to all staff on top of their salary and we also offer additional annual leave after 1 year of tenure (from 20 to 25 days a year) that continues to grow another day each year of service until you max out at 30 days per year.
title: Marketing Data Analyst

description:
12 Months Max Term Contract

Engage with complex data and drive meaningful change

Leverage your expertise to transform analytics into meaningful strategic recommendations

Tennis Australia is embarking on a phase of Digital Transformation, and as a result, an opportunity has emerged for a Data Analyst. The Digital Transformation Program will establish new digital experiences, foundational capabilities and strategic enablers. Unified Digital Experience will cover Web and Mobile Digital Presence for Tennis Australia. This digital experience will enhance how our customers find courts, coaches and tournaments, participate in Leagues and Tournaments, manage their rating and ranking, and administrators and deliverers who organise and deliver Tennis.

If you need assistance or adjustments to participate in the application process fully, please contact recruit@tennis.com.au.

About The Role

Join Tennis Australia as an experienced Data Analyst and help transform complex datasets into actionable insights that drive business decisions. In this role, you'll utilise tools like SQL, Python/R, and Web Analytics to create reports and dashboards that inform stakeholders and executives. Collaborate closely with various teams to unlock the value of data and support a culture of data-driven decision-making across the organisation.

In this role, you will:

Data Analytics - Support the delivery of digital analytics, mapping, code/error management, and scripting to assist internal stakeholders and initiatives.


 * Understand the use of Google Cloud Platform (GCP), Google Marketing Platform tools, SEO, web crawlers, and other resources that facilitate digital analytics.
 * Monitor, track, and develop dashboards and benchmark reports based on stakeholder requirements
 * Understand and establish data models that shape digital analytics capabilities.
   
   
   

Development of Customer Insights and Data Library -Develop tools and reports to monitor key performance indicators across the enterprise


 * Analyze customer data using cloud tools to create large data sets.
 * Generate and present fact-based customer and product performance insights to improve engagement and personalization models.
 * Combine data from various sources to generate insights.
   
   
   

Data Analysis - Improve decision-making by applying market knowledge to influence strategic direction.


 * Create advanced data models to solve complex issues and provide insightful analyses.
 * Translate data insights into actionable recommendations, presenting information clearly and persuasively.
   
   
   

Customer Analytics, Marketing Automation and CRM - Utilize modern data science and machine learning techniques within a CRM context.


 * Create dashboards and reports to generate actionable insights.
 * Use analytics to enhance CRM marketing strategies, focusing on profitability, lifetime value, loyalty, and ROI.
 * Develop predictive capabilities for segmentation and modelling to improve customer retention and acquisition.
 * Design target groups for CRM campaigns and help the marketing team optimize testing by analysing campaign performance across customer segments.
   
   
   

About You

What you will bring to the role:


 * Strong capabilities in time management, planning, and prioritisation.
 * Extensive hands-on knowledge and experience with tools and techniques for analysis, data manipulation, and presentation (such as SQL, web analytics tools, Python, data visualization, and web/app design and coding).
 * Ability to adapt to cloud technologies and systems for managing and manipulating data analytics across diverse channels.
 * Experience in database analysis and data extraction techniques.
 * Excellent communication skills, able to translate and communicate data insights into actionable business recommendations for a diverse audience.
 * Proven experience in working to derive valuable insights, as well as visualizing these insights for both technical and non-technical stakeholders.
 * Ability to maintain composure under pressure while working in a dynamic and challenging environment.
 * A strong curiosity to analyse data and translate findings into business insights and recommendations.
 * Demonstrates initiative, recommends best practices, and determination to ensure the fulfilment of goals.
 * Effective collaboration within a team environment
 * You must hold (or be willing to obtain) a current Police Check and Working with Children Check.
   
   
   

What’s in it for you?


 * Career development with a range of formal education and on-the-job training opportunities
 * Tickets to the Australian Open
 * Monthly health & wellbeing activities through our Thrive program.
 * Onsite gym & tennis facilities
 * Flexible working practices
 * Free car parking
 * A range of discounts from our sponsorship partners
