description:
Data Scientist – Mapping Australia’s Political Landscape




Kotti Capital is the single family office of a first generation Australian entrepreneur.




About the Role

Are you passionate about understanding the intricate dynamics of Australia’s political landscape? We’re looking for a talented Data Scientist to lead a groundbreaking project aimed at creating a comprehensive graph of Australia’s political ecosystem. This graph will map key individuals, their core beliefs, and ideas, assigning weights and relationships to uncover insights into political structures, ideologies, and networks.

This role combines cutting-edge data science techniques with social and political analysis to deliver a powerful tool for understanding the nation’s political framework.




Key Responsibilities
 * Data Collection & Integration: Identify, gather, and pre-process data from diverse sources, including public records, media articles, academic papers, and social media, to build the foundation for the graph.
 * Graph Construction: Design and develop a dynamic graph structure that maps relationships between political figures, their beliefs, affiliations, and influence.
 * Weight Assignment: Develop algorithms to assign and adjust weights based on factors such as ideological alignment, historical patterns, social influence, and policy focus.
 * Data Analysis & Visualisation: Use advanced analytics and visualisation techniques to uncover trends, clusters, and patterns within the political landscape.
 * Model Refinement: Continuously refine the graph and weighting system to ensure accuracy, relevance, and responsiveness to new data.
 * Stakeholder Collaboration: Work closely with political analysts, researchers, and other stakeholders to contextualise findings and ensure meaningful insights.




Qualifications & Skills
 * Educational Background: Bachelor’s or Master’s degree in Data Science, Computer Science, Mathematics, Political Science, or related fields. Advanced degrees are a plus.
 * Technical Expertise:
 * Proficiency in programming languages such as Python or R.
 * Strong knowledge of graph databases (e.g. Neo4j) and libraries like NetworkX.
 * Experience with machine learning and natural language processing (NLP) for text analysis.
 * Familiarity with data visualisation tools like Tableau, Gephi, or D3.js.
 * Analytical Skills: Ability to interpret complex datasets and develop actionable insights.
 * Understanding of Australian Politics: A strong interest or background in political science, especially in the Australian context, is highly desirable.
 * Communication Skills: Ability to explain technical findings to non-technical audiences and contribute to multidisciplinary discussions.




What We Offer
 * Impactful Work: Be at the forefront of a project that could shape how Australians understand their political environment.
 * Innovative Environment: Collaborate with leading experts in data science and political analysis.
 * Flexibility: Hybrid work options to suit your lifestyle.
 * Growth Opportunities: Access to professional development resources and opportunities to lead cutting-edge initiatives.




How to Apply

If you’re excited by the prospect of blending data science with political analysis to create meaningful change, we want to hear from you!

Please send your CV, a cover letter outlining your interest in this role, and examples of relevant work (e.g. data visualisation projects, predictive models, or analyses) to malisa@kotti.capital

Applications close Friday 17 January 2025.

Description

Who we are:

FleetPartners Group is an ASX 300 listed financial services, vehicle management, and employee benefits company. We are an organisation where 98% of all team members believe that their manager genuinely cares about their well-being and feels valued. We also help everyday Australians to maximise their salary by administering employee benefit programs and help them to get into the car of their dreams.

We have a strong company culture that values our people and are proud to present you with this opportunity to join our team. We support all types and sizes of businesses to acquire and effectively manage their vehicles, with over 93,000 vehicles currently under management.

Our Promise

FleetPartners Group is an equal opportunities employer; therefore, all qualified applicants will receive consideration without regard to their race, colour, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, disability, or status as a protected veteran.

Who We’re Looking For

This role reports to the Risk Manager of passenger and light commercial vehicle assets and involves setting and managing the end of lease (residual) value of vehicles and maintenance budgets for FleetPartners Australia and New Zealand. The role is also responsible for reporting on lease portfolio metrics, maintaining the integrity and quality of vehicle attribute and sales data, managing internal data repositories, and supporting the broader risk department. (Note: this is not an IT or business analyst role).

Key Deliverables

What you’ll be doing:


 * Day to day residual value and maintenance recommendations in support of Sales team for customer quotation or competitive tenders
 * Review and recommend residual value positions for all vehicles to be quoted by the business
 * Recommend maintenance budgets for all quotable vehicles within various asset classes
 * Ad hoc portfolio analysis to support business decisions
 * Proactively identify opportunities to improve day-to-day processes
 * Run monthly valuations of current portfolio, analyse outputs and provide insights
   
   

This Will Be Achieved Through


 * Analysis of large volumes of motor vehicle sales data to identify price trends and movements to set residual values at end of lease
 * Utilising Excel for analysis, modelling and calculation of forecast residual values in a complex matrix of multiple variables
 * Being familiar with motor vehicle specifications and knowledge of vehicle market trends to support the data analysis and residual value setting process
 * Support business to manage both residual value and maintenance risks across the designated portfolios and maintain residual value and maintenance tables in the relevant system
 * Extensive data analysis and collaborative engagement with internal and external stakeholders and working within a small team environment
   
   

Requirements

We’re looking for someone who’s…


 * Tertiary qualified in a quantitative or commercial discipline e.g. Finance, Mathematics, Statistics, Economics or similar
 * Working experience in a commercial analytical role including valuation, forecasting, pricing and costing
 * Working experience with SAS Enterprise Guide, SQL & Microsoft Office Suite
 * An appreciation of motor vehicles
 * Sound experience in the quantitative analysis of data and application of qualitative insight to derive forecast valuations
 * Experience in leasing or automotive sector would be advantageous
 * Analytical and conceptual in nature with a passion for using data to elicit key insights and trends
 * Strong communication and interpersonal skills in dealing with multiple stakeholders
 * Desire to present new ideas and challenge the status quo to drive continuous improvement
 * Ability to work well under pressure, handle multiple concurrent tasks, meet deadlines and deliver results
 * Attention to detail
 * Highly organised and self-motivated, able to work autonomously or in groups without the need for managerial supervision
 * Ability to provide evidence-based recommendations to internal and external stakeholders
   
   

If you do not have all the requirements for this role, however, feel that you would be a good fit, we encourage you to apply.

Benefits

We offer:


 * We are always developing our benefits for our staff, this includes up to 27 days annual leave, flu jabs, corporate discounts and hybrid working arrangements.
 * We like to see our team grow, develop and succeed at FleetPartners; therefore, we pride ourselves with providing promotion and secondment opportunities.
 * We like our team to enjoy their working environment and culture, we do this by quarterly recognition awards, office/ external events and by celebrating our core C-A-R-E values.
   
   

Next Steps

If you are successful in your application, then we will be in touch with you soon.

Offer of employment with FleetPartners Group is conditioned upon the successful completion of a background check, subject to applicable laws and regulations.

We are seeking a highly skilled and experienced Data Scientist to help drive our Process Mining and Process Excellence activities across the Asia Pacific region. You will be responsible for engaging with our clients' teams to identify, extract, and transform data elements that will drive our Process Intelligence and Process Excellence initiatives. You will work closely with the Director of Process Mining and Process Excellence to develop and implement data-driven strategies to improve operational efficiency, enhance business outcomes, and contribute to overall growth and profitability.




The ideal candidate will have a minimum of 5 years of experience in the field, with a strong track record of managing client relationships, understanding complex data environments, and delivering process mining solutions that drive measurable business value. Strong technical skills in data extraction, cleansing, and modeling are required. Knowledge of process mining tools such as Celonis, Apromore, Appian or UiPath is highly valuable. A solid understanding of business processes, excellent problem-solving skills, and the ability to communicate complex insights effectively are essential for success in this role.




You will be responsible for developing business opportunities by identifying and extracting key data elements that will be used as inputs into Process Mining technologies. You will ensure that the extracted data is optimized for use in process mining, leveraging your knowledge of data architecture and integration methodologies to create efficient and scalable solutions.




From a service offering perspective, you will support the identification of market trends and emerging client demands for specific services in the Data space. You will also contribute to the development of the offering and act as a key point of contact for both the sales and delivery organizations. You will be responsible for identifying and growing opportunities by leveraging your expertise to tailor solutions that address unique client challenges, ultimately leading to tangible improvements in operational efficiency and business outcomes.




Responsibilities & tasks for this role:




• Engage with clients to identify, extract, cleanse, and prepare data for use in Process Mining applications.

• Analyze client data to identify patterns, insights, and opportunities for process optimization.

• Develop data models to facilitate process analysis and improvement initiatives.

• Create impactful visualizations and reports to communicate findings and recommendations to both technical and non-technical stakeholders.

• Manage multiple engagements simultaneously, ensuring successful project delivery within scope.

• Collaborate with clients to understand their business processes and ensure data-driven insights are aligned with their strategic goals.

• Collaborate with other leaders in the company to ensure a cohesive approach to business development and client management.

• Stay up to date on industry trends and best practices, and ensure that we are continuously improving our offerings.

• Mentor junior team members in data science methodologies and best practices, fostering skill development and knowledge sharing across the team.

• Identify opportunities to leverage advanced analytics, such as machine learning, to drive further value from process mining initiatives.




Must-have qualifications & competencies:




• Minimum of 5 years of experience as a Data Scientist

• Bachelors degree in a relevant field

• Expertise in data extraction, cleansing, and modeling using tools like SQL, Python, or R.

• Strong knowledge of business processes, operations, and identifying areas for optimization.

• Experience in optimizing data for use in analytics and process mining, understanding data pipelines, architecture, and integration methodologies.

• Ability to manage multiple projects simultaneously, ensuring they are delivered on time, within scope, and on budget.

• Proven experience in managing client relationships and acting as a trusted advisor, effectively guiding stakeholders through data-driven insights.

• Strong analytical mindset with a track record of deriving actionable insights from complex data sets and identifying opportunities for process improvement.

description:
Social Research Centre Graduate Program - opportunities available in Quantitative Research, Evaluation and Qualitative Research, Data Science, and Statistics and Methods.




Are you passionate about making a real impact on society? Do you want to understand and help solve the challenges of our rapidly evolving world? The Graduate Program at the Social Research Centre is your chance to turn curiosity into action.




Why choose the Social Research Centre?

The Social Research Centre is Australia's largest dedicated social research and evaluation agency. Our team includes a dedicated statistics and survey methods team, data scientists and programmers, evaluation and qualitative research specialists, as well as Australia's only probability-based online panel - Life in Australia™.

For over 20 years, we’ve brought together a dynamic team of experts and innovative thinkers to tackle society’s biggest challenges. We conduct research that truly matters—projects that drive change, shape conversations, and leave a lasting positive impact on our communities. If you’re all about action, innovation, and creating a better future, that’s exactly what we stand for.




What makes our program unique?

As an end-to-end research organisation, we give graduates the chance to experience every aspect of social research – from quantitative research to evaluation, qualitative research, data science, and statistics and analytics.




Here’s what’s in it for you:

 * Hands-on industry experience: Work on interesting and impactful projects
 * Structured rotation program: Explore diverse research methods and analytical techniques
 * Training and development: Build the skills and knowledge you need to thrive
 * Supportive mentoring: Work alongside experienced professionals who’ll guide your growth
 * Career path: Complete the program and join one of our world-class teams
 * Perks: Recruitment referral bonuses, annual flu vaccinations, Employee Assistance Program, regular social events




This is your chance to learn by doing and build skills that set you apart. Whether you're passionate about people, data, or finding creative solutions, this program will help you grow.




What you’ll be doing:

 * Research Design: Craft quantitative and qualitative research methodologies
 * Hands-On Fieldwork: Conduct surveys, interviews, and focus groups
 * Data Skills: Analyse and interpret quantitative and qualitative data
 * Project Management: Plan and manage research projects




This role is based in Melbourne CBD.




Who should apply?

We’re looking for curious, motivated graduates who want to make an impact. If you check these boxes, this program could be for you:

 * You’re in your final year of uni or finished your degree within the last two years. Relevant degrees include Social Sciences, Psychology, Public Health, Sociology, Data Science, Statistics, Mathematics, Computer Science, Public Policy, Economics or other related disciplines demonstrating analytical or research capabilities
 * You’re an Australian or New Zealand citizen or an Australian permanent resident




What we’re looking for in you:

 * Eye for Detail: You spot the small things that matter and love solving problems
 * Strong Communicator: You’re clear and confident, whether writing or speaking
 * Organised and Efficient: You manage your time well and can handle multiple tasks
 * Team Player: Works well independently and collaboratively, ready to support the team
 * Cool Under Pressure: You stay focused and helpful even when things get busy
 * Positive and Adaptable: You bring energy and flexibility to every challenge
 * Eager to Learn: You’re motivated to pick up new skills and take on new opportunities
 * Passion for Social Research: You care about making a difference and want to build a career that creates positive change

Bonus points if you’ve got:

 * A basic understanding of research, survey and/or statistical methods
 * Familiarity with software such as SPSS, Stata, Q, R, Python or SQL




If this sounds like you, we’d love to have you on the team!




What’s next?

Ready to make your mark on Australian society? Upload your resume, academic transcripts, and a one-page pitch telling us why you’re the perfect fit for our team. No strict deadlines—once the roles are filled, they’re gone, so it’s the perfect time to jump on board.




For more information, contact recruitment@srcentre.com.au or visit our careers page.




The Social Research Centre values diversity and believes that an inclusive and fair work environment has a positive impact on the wellbeing of employees, job satisfaction and productivity. We encourage people of Aboriginal and/or Torres Strait Islander heritage, people with diverse cultural and linguistic backgrounds, sexual orientation, gender identity and people with disability to apply.

description:
Velrada is Microsoft's number 1 global partner in Dynamics 365 Field Services technology, transforming Healthcare, Asset Intensive and Local Government organizations using the latest in D365, Power Platform, Azure and Data/AI solutions. Our advisory team, comprised of top analysts who are also leaders in the company, complement our technical delivery teams by consulting directly with our customers’ C-level executives and developing strategic roadmaps for their success.




In March of 2022 Velrada was acquired by NRI. Founded in 1965, NRI is a leading global provider of consulting services and system solutions, including management consulting, system integration, and IT management and solutions for the financial, manufacturing, retail and service industries. Clients from all layers of these individual industries partner with NRI to tap NRI’s research expertise and innovative solutions across the organization to expand businesses, design corporate structures and create new business strategies. NRI has more than 13,000 employees in more than 70 offices globally including New York, London, Tokyo, Hong Kong, Singapore, and Australia. NRI reports annual sales above $4.9 billion. NRI is rated “A” by S&P Global Ratings Japan.




Location: Melbourne, Sydney, Brisbane, Adelaide or Perth.




Role Purpose

The Business Intelligence (BI) Lead plays a pivotal role in delivering best-in-class data visualization solutions using Microsoft Power BI within Microsoft Fabric. This role is responsible for designing, implementing, and optimizing BI systems, facilitating workshops to gather requirements, migrating existing BI solutions to Power BI, and delivering high-quality dashboards and reports that empower data-driven decision-making. The BI Lead is also a key contributor to the governance, administration, and security of BI platforms within the organization.







Key Responsibilities

1. BI Solution Development

 * Develop and implement end-to-end BI solutions within Microsoft Fabric, focusing on Power BI.
 * Build and maintain Power BI datasets, data models, and reports to deliver actionable insights.
 * Create advanced calculations using DAX and Power Query for data transformation and optimization.
 * Leverage Power BI premium features such as Paginated Reports, calculation groups, and Tabular Editor to deliver enterprise-grade solutions.
 * Ensure best practices are followed for report design, visualization, and user experience.







2. System Migration and Optimization

 * Lead the migration of BI systems from tools such as Tableau and Qlik to Power BI, SSIS, SSRS ensuring seamless transitions and minimal disruption to business operations.
 * Analyze existing dashboards, datasets, and workflows in legacy tools and reimagine them in Power BI to enhance performance and user experience.
 * Provide clear migration roadmaps, including timelines, resource allocation, and training for users transitioning to Power BI.
 * Optimize BI system performance by fine-tuning data models, report layouts, and query efficiency post-migration.







3. System Implementation and Documentation

 * Test, implement, and document BI systems, ensuring scalability and robustness.
 * Collaborate with teams to establish comprehensive documentation for workflows, datasets, and governance practices.
 * Contribute to the organization’s BI knowledge base, documenting Power BI Premium features and advanced administration techniques.







4. Stakeholder Engagement and Workshop Facilitation

 * Facilitate requirements-gathering workshops with business stakeholders to define reporting needs and BI strategies.
 * Translate business requirements into scalable and optimized BI solutions.
 * Present data visualization solutions to customers, highlighting value and actionable insights.







5. Administration, Governance, and Security

 * Manage Power BI workspaces, apps, and user access within the Fabric service.
 * Define and enforce administration and governance policies for BI solutions, ensuring compliance with organizational standards.
 * Implement robust security measures for BI systems, protecting sensitive data and maintaining user roles and permissions.







6. Leadership and Mentorship

 * Mentor and guide junior team members in developing expertise in Power BI and associated tools.
 * Foster a culture of continuous learning and improvement in BI visualization and modeling techniques.
 * Lead internal training sessions on Power BI Premium features, DAX, Power Query, and Fabric service best practices.







7. Innovation and Optimization

 * Drive innovation in data visualization by exploring emerging features within Microsoft Fabric and Power BI.
 * Leverage advanced features such as calculation groups, Tabular Editor, and AI-powered insights to deliver cutting-edge solutions.
 * Continuously explore opportunities for automation and process improvements in BI workflows.







Key Performance Indicators (KPIs)

 * Customer Satisfaction: Deliver visually compelling, actionable reports that exceed stakeholder expectations.
 * Solution Scalability: Create BI systems that are robust, scalable, and optimized for performance.
 * Migration Success: Seamless transition of legacy BI solutions (e.g., Tableau, Qlik) to Power BI, with improved usability and performance.
 * Governance and Security: Ensure adherence to BI governance and security standards.
 * Innovation: Adoption of emerging Power BI features and tools to continuously improve BI solutions.







Preferred Skills and Qualifications

Technical Expertise

 * Expert-level experience with Power BI, DAX, SSIS, SSRS and Power Query, and SQL as well as Microsoft Fabric
 * Proficiency in data modeling, creating optimized datasets, and advanced data transformations.
 * Strong knowledge of Power BI Premium features, including Paginated Reports, Tabular Editor, and calculation groups.
 * Hands-on experience with Power BI within Microsoft Fabric, including workspaces, apps, and user access.
 * Proven track record of migrating BI systems from Tableau and Qlik to Power BI.
 * Experience implementing governance frameworks, security protocols, and administration policies for BI systems.




Soft Skills

 * Strong facilitation skills for workshops and requirement gathering.
 * Excellent verbal and written communication skills, particularly for presenting insights to customers.
 * Ability to collaborate across technical and non-technical teams, aligning business needs with BI capabilities.




Certifications

 * Microsoft Certified: Data Analyst Associate or Power BI Data Analyst (preferred).
 * Certifications in Microsoft Fabric or related Power BI Premium features (desirable).







Next steps:

If you want to be part of a growing Management & IT Consultancy where you are appreciated, work with like-minded peers and continue to grow your skills and learn then please do get in touch for a confidential discussion.

Please apply via this advert.

Velrada is an equal opportunities employer, we are proud of our diverse workforce. We encourage applications from all suitable candidates.




Have a look at our website for more information and details on our organization – www.velrada.com



Velrada tend to receive many applications for our job openings and at this stage are only able to respond to successful applicants.



Please note: we are not accepting applications or CV’s from recruitment companies.
title: Business Intelligence (BI) Lead – Data Visualization

description:
What You'll Do:

We are seeking a talented and motivated Data Analyst to support our

commercial teams in Australia, within the broader Pacific region. As part of our

APAC Analytics team, your role will be pivotal in harnessing our extensive

shopper and retailer data, combined with a deep understanding of performance

marketing and retail media technology, to provide actionable insights and

recommendations to some of the largest retailers and brands in Australia.

In this role, you'll have privileged access to one of the world's largest datasets,

alongside the computational power required to deliver insights into shopper

behavior, market trends, and product performance that can't be found anywhere

else.

The scope of this role involves technically rigorous work, including the use of

leading-edge data analysis technologies and daily interaction with other cross-

functional business units and external clients. Criteo’s high-growth business

model brings both opportunities and challenges. The ideal candidate functions

with minimal oversight and has the ability to learn new concepts quickly.


 * Performance Optimization: You will analyze complex data from multiple sources to gain a comprehensive understanding of campaign and retailer performance, detect root causes of issues, identify growth opportunities, and generate innovative and impactful insights for our clients.
 * Strategic Client Support: As the sole Data Analyst for Australia, you will collaborate closely with the commercial and technical teams to support and cultivate deep strategic relationships with clients, guiding their strategies and aligning with their long-term goals.
 * Reporting Tools and Metrics: You will develop and scale reports and metrics that provide actionable insights to various teams across the organization, including strategic leadership teams.
 * Testing: You will design, monitor, and analyze A/B tests to gain deeper insights into how our products perform for our clients.
 * Collaborative Projects: Collaborating on ad hoc projects with different teams (Commercial, Operations, Product, R&D, teams...) from different regions, you will automate analyses on a global scale, enhance internal processes, streamline workflows, and disseminate knowledge throughout the company.
 * Expertise Development: In parallel, you will develop a deep understanding of the online marketing ecosystem, with a strong emphasis on the retail media sector, while also providing support to our broader performance marketing business. Simultaneously, you will refine your analytical skills, devising new models and automation schemes to drive continuous improvement.
 * Australia Representation: You will represent Australia within the broader APAC Analytics community, ensuring that the country's insights and learnings are effectively shared across the APAC region.
   
   
   

Who You Are:

Your work experience: 3+ years in an analytical role in Technology, Consulting,

with a good understanding of internet advertising technologies (cookies, DSP,

SSP, RTB, etc.)

Your academic background: Bachelor’s degree or equivalent in a quantitative

or business discipline, with a primary emphasis on Analytics (Statistics,

Mathematics, Computer Science, and related areas....).

Your Analytics skills: You possess a comprehensive grasp of relational

databases, data architecture/governance, and the practical application of

statistical concepts, especially within a testing context. Your strength lies in your

exceptional attention to detail, complemented by your capacity to envision the

broader strategic picture.

Your technical skills: You have hands-on experience in working with databases,

have some programming experience, and are a fast learner. SQL and Python are

a must. Bonus point if you have experience in using technologies such as

Hadoop, Hive, Vertica, Tableau.

Your business skills: You are client-focused, able to create and convey clear

messages and straightforward recommendations, and have experience in

discussing with clients. You are able to explain technical concepts to a non-

technical audience. Engaging with clients and holding discussions is a crucial

aspect of this position.

Your personality: You are versatile, autonomous, able to multi-task and

prioritize; you like to interact and collaborate with people from various

backgrounds, mindsets, and cultures.

We acknowledge that many candidates may not meet every single role requirement listed above. If your experience looks a little different from our requirements but you believe that you can still bring value to the role, we’d love to see your application!

Who We Are:

Criteo is the global commerce media company that enables marketers and media owners to deliver richer consumer experiences and drive better commerce outcomes through its industry leading Commerce Media Platform.

At Criteo, our culture is as unique as it is diverse. From our offices around the world or from home, our incredible team of 3,600 Criteos collaborates to develop an open and inclusive environment. We seek to ensure that all of our workers are treated equally, and we do not tolerate discrimination based on race, gender identity, gender, sexual orientation, color, national origin, religion, age, disability, political opinion, pregnancy, migrant status, ethnicity, marital or family status, or other protected characteristics at all stages of the employment lifecycle including how we attract and recruit, through promotions, pay decisions, benefits, career progression and development. We aim to ensure employment decisions and actions are based solely on business-related considerations and not on protected characteristics. As outlined in our Code of Business Conduct and Ethics, we strictly forbid any kind of discrimination, harassment, mistreatment or bullying towards colleagues, clients, suppliers, stakeholders, shareholders, or any visitors of Criteo. All of this supports us in our mission to power the world’s marketers with trusted and impactful advertising encouraging discovery, innovation and choice in an open internet.

Why Join Us:

At Criteo, we take pride in being a caring culture and are committed to providing our employees with valuable benefits that support their physical, emotional and financial wellbeing, their interests and the important life events. We aim to create a place where people can grow and learn from each other while having a meaningful impact. We want to set you up for success in your job, and an important part of that includes comprehensive perks & benefits. Benefits may vary depending on the country where you work and the nature of your employment with Criteo. When determining compensation, we carefully consider a wide range of job-related factors, including experience, knowledge, skills, education, and location. These factors can cause your compensation to vary.

description:
Company Description

Are you ready to be a big part of something big?

At carsales, we're all about making buying and selling a great experience. For 25 years we’ve been evolving with the new economy to help people choose how they move today and tomorrow.

When it comes to your career, we want to provide big opportunities to help you make a big impact. But for this to be possible, we strive to feel small. Small enough to quickly change tack, small enough to learn from different departments and small enough to connect authentically with leadership.

Our Data Team has embarked on an exciting phase of transformation, they work across all parts of our digital business.

Not something you’d expect from one of the country’s biggest tech companies, is it?

And one of the best parts? We give you the autonomy to choose the working location that best suits your lifestyle – Office, Hybrid or Anywhere.

What’s on offer:


 * A place where you can move your career forward, where you’ll be continuously backed to make new ideas happen, and the chance to do work that makes real, significant impact in the world.
 * We’re proud to be recognised as one of Australia’s Best Workplaces™ by Great Place to Work®, a Family Friendly Workplace, a WORK180 endorsed employer for women and WGEA Employer of Choice for Gender Equality
 * The support of a highly engaged, high-performing team including a leadership team that’s you’ll actually have face time with.
 * 22 weeks paid parental leave for primary caregivers, four weeks paid secondary caregivers leave, six weeks paid gender affirming care leave.
   
   

Job Description

What you’ll do:

This is your opportunity to grow at the intersection of Data, Digital, Product, Technology and human behavioral change to be a big part of something big.


 * Share expertise to define carsales' Retail team's analytical approaches underpinning product performance and development, data commercialisation, data-enabled partnerships and commercial outcomes.
 * Develop and support solutions that deliver end-to-end data products and direct the lifecycle of complex solutions.
 * Collaborate and connect with teams across Data, Retail, Product and Technology to deliver on decision-support and data commercialisation initiatives as a data SME.
 * Understand and agree to the medium-term (~3-12 month) plans in Retail and Product and break these down into quarterly OKRs that can be executed by smaller teams.
 * Share expertise to grow and deliver as a key leader within the Data function, bringing best-in-industry analytical expertise in partnering with our Retail function whose opportunities are amongst the fastest growing in the business.
 * Share expertise to perform advanced statistical modelling and analysis of structured and unstructured datasets to develop metrics, reports and visualizations of trends and patterns.
 * Lead teams of 1-3 data specialists that deliver cross-functional work with business and technology teams.
   
   

Qualifications

What are we looking for?

What are we looking for?


 * Demonstrated inclusive and interpersonal attributes that connect you to our behaviours (we change the game, we own it, we step in, we are curious, we don’t take ourselves too seriously).
 * Demonstrate understanding and expertise to advance our analytical solutions (e.g. machine learning, product development, digital analytics, cross-site performance optimisation) that enables carsales' Retail division's continued market leadership against a backdrop of evolving market conditions.
 * Expertise in the application of quantitative methods and/or other developing econometric / statistical type solutions.
 * Collaborative communication with visualisation tools and techniques to generate dashboards and outputs that aid in data storytelling, understanding and interpretation of trends and patterns of business importance.
 * Collaborative skills to manage and solve complex trade-offs between business stakeholder needs and technical objectives, and a willingness to engage in conversations between groups.
 * Skilled in two or more programming languages of their area of specialisation –– e.g. SQL, Python, Java, Scala and experience with cloud data platforms and analytic tools including – Snowflake, dbt, Thoughtspot, Tableau.
   
   

Additional Information

A few other things we want to let you know about...


 * carsales is an equal opportunity employer and we pride ourselves on fostering a diverse and inclusive workplace. We encourage everyone of all ages, genders and backgrounds to apply. If you’re a candidate with a disability or you’ll need some adjustments to be at your best, let us know how we can provide you with additional support.
 * We know how important keeping that balance between work/life is and have a range of flexible working options on offer, including part time work. We are open to this conversation during our recruitment process - if you want to know more just ask.
 * We are a proud Circle Back Initiative Employer which means we are committed to responding to every job applicant.
 * Successful candidates joining the carsales family are required to undergo a National Police Record check and must have full-time Australian working rights on an ongoing basis.
   
   

So come and join our team - because every role is a big role in our plans to go big.
title: Analytics Principal

description:
Data Analysts the design, analysis and delivery of relevant, trusted and objective statistics and data-related insights.

The Data Analyst should have experience in the areas of SAS migration/upgrades, data quality profiling, and exposure to metadata management practices and tools such as Aristotle or other data cataloguing solutions. The role assists with the management of the organisation’s data assets to ensure data is discoverable, understood and of appropriate quality. The analyst uncovers and where appropriate documents customers’ data requirements and is able to:

Conduct data quality analysis and curate/ transform data present in DataLake/Teradata to support reporting needs

Generate data quality profiles using SAS data management tools, Teradata and/or Data Lake

Use SAS tools such as QKB to identify duplicate records and implement matching scenarios

Develop reporting to visualise data quality profiling results and to support the use and management of data catalogues using tools such as Power BI and Tableau.

Senior Data Analysts work under the limited direction of senior staff. They exercise both initiative and judgement in the interpretation of policy and in the application of practices and procedures. Decision making is dependent on judgement, skills and knowledge. Senior Data Analysts manage and organise their own work in the context of competing priorities, including contributing to business planning, changes in workplace practices and business improvement strategies.

Duties may include some or all of the following:


 * Evaluating, defining, integrating and organising data coming from multiple operational systems
 * Performing administrative, technical and customising tasks in the data environment
 * Controlling and assisting with the data management process, including loading, creating maintaining, analysing and distributing data
 * Resolving data integration issues related to data in their area of expertise
 * Developing and maintaining reports, dashboards and other visualisations to support data governance and data management processes
 * Collaborating with stakeholders to resolve issues and ensure effective, timely implementation of projects
 * Monitor workloads to ensure business goals are achieved
 * Assist in the processing of data, including matching and maintaining specific object data
 * Develop data standards and provide input to strategy for the solution
 * Assist in development of, and execution of, data quality programmes
 * Contribute to the development and implementation of improvements and best practice in processes and procedures
 * Contribute to relevant business and people planning, and develop local strategies to improve against key performance measures
 * Prepare correspondence such as reports, corporate and technical documentation for review by executive level staff
 * Resolve or escalate issues as required and suggest alternative approaches
 * Exercise appropriate delegation in accordance with legislation and guidelines
   
   

Technical skills


 * Experience in data analysis including data governance and data management in government/public sector or industry equivalent. 2. Experience in at least one of the following tools - Data Lake, HUE, SAS, SQL, Aged Care, EDW/Teradata, Mainframe, Tableau. 3. Working knowledge of Data Lake, Hadoop, EDW, Cloudera and Hue. 4. Experience in designing and delivering data analytics solutions for large and complex projects.
   
   

Mandatory Criteria


 * Business intelligence: Level 3 (SFIA)
   
   

Sources and prepares data for analysis and performs standard business intelligence analysis activities. Creates and delivers standard reports in accordance with stakeholder needs and conforming to agreed standards. Investigates the need for new or revised business intelligence analysis. Contributes to the recommendation of improvements. Engages with stakeholders under direction.


 * Business situation analysis: Level 5 (SFIA)
   
   

Plans, manages and investigates business situation analysis where there is significant ambiguity and complexity. Advises on the approach and techniques to be used for business situation analysis. Ensures holistic view adopted to identify and analyse wide-ranging problems and opportunities. Engages and collaborates with a wide range of stakeholders, including those at the management level. Gains agreement from stakeholders to conclusions and recommendations. Contributes to definition of organisational standards and guidelines for business situation analysis.


 * Data communication: Level 3 (DCF)
   
   

Can develop and deliver advanced level narrative to communicate insights drawn from complex data sources and outputs Maintains understanding of new trends and innovations relating to data communication (including Artificial Intelligence-based technologies) and develops skills in these where relevant Understands the importance of translating technical concepts into non-technical language, and can adapt communication effectively for a range of audiences. Can use innovative approaches to improve the process of summarising data into meaningful narratives Uses high quality analytics and visualisation to communicate insights from data Can effectively listen to technical and business stakeholders, and understand and interpret their data needs


 * Data management: Level 4 (SFIA)
   
   

Devises and implements master data management processes for specific subsets of data. Assesses the integrity of data from multiple sources. Provides advice on the transformation of data from one format/medium to another. Maintains and implements information handling procedures. Enables the availability, integrity and searchability of information through the application of formal data and metadata structures and protection measures.


 * Data modelling and design: Level 4 (SFIA)
   
   

Investigates enterprise data requirements where there is some complexity and ambiguity. Plans own data modelling and design activities, selecting appropriate techniques and the correct level of detail for meeting assigned objectives. Provides advice and guidance to others using the data structures and associated components.


 * Data outputs, products or services: Level 3 (DCF)
   
   

Has expert knowledge about the production of a data output, product or service Provides expertise in developing new products or data services to meet evolving requirements, needs and opportunities. Can build the capability of others in the delivery of data outputs, products or services


 * Data visualisation: Level 4 (SFIA)
   
   

Applies a variety of visualisation techniques and designs the content and appearance of data visuals. Operationalises and automates activities for efficient and timely production of data visuals. Selects appropriate visualisation approaches from a range of applicable options. Contributes to exploration and experimentation in data visualisation.


 * Database design: Level 3 (SFIA)
   
   

Interprets installation standards to meet project needs and produces database or data warehouse component specifications. Develops appropriate physical database or data warehouse design elements, within set policies, to meet data requirements.


 * Identify research questions: Level 3 (DCF)
   
   

Uses a range of techniques to assess data needs and identify gaps, towards the formulation of appropriate research questions


 * Integrate data: Level 2 (DCF)
   
   

Can perform data integration using standard tools and can implement quality controls Knows where to obtain expert advice on data integration as needed Is able to understand and amend existing code (programming language) to integrate data Can assess datasets' suitability for linkage and extract appropriately prepared datasets


 * Programming/software development: Level 3 (SFIA)
   
   

Designs, codes, verifies, tests, documents, amends and refactors moderately complex programs/scripts. Applies agreed standards and tools to achieve a well-engineered result. Monitors and reports on progress. Identifies issues related to software development activities. Proposes practical solutions to resolve issues. Collaborates in reviews of work with others as appropriate.


 * Statistical data analysis: Level 3 (DCF)
   
   

Contributes to the development of new functionality for statistical analysis applications, which enables new ways of doing things Can write custom scripts and code in a statistical computing language to conduct complex analytical tasks Maintains understanding of new trends and innovations relating to statistical data analysis (including Artificial Intelligence-based technologies) and develops skills in these where relevant


 * Subject matter expertise: Level 3 (DCF)
   
   

Is an expert resource on the subject matter area associated with data use, including understanding and influencing the effective use of the data within that subject matter area and the relationship between that use and other data use contexts

Senior Data Analysts work under the limited direction of senior staff. They exercise both initiative and judgement in the interpretation of policy and in the application of practices and procedures. Decision making is dependent on judgement, skills and knowledge. Senior Data Analysts manage and organise their own work in the context of competing priorities, including contributing to business planning, changes in workplace practices and business improvement strategies.

Duties may include some or all of the following:


 * Evaluating, defining, integrating and organising data coming from multiple operational systems
 * Performing administrative, technical and customising tasks in the data environment
 * Controlling and assisting with the data management process, including loading, creating maintaining, analysing and distributing data
 * Resolving data integration issues related to data in their area of expertise
 * Developing and maintaining reports, dashboards and other visualisations to support data governance and data management processes
 * Collaborating with stakeholders to resolve issues and ensure effective, timely implementation of projects
 * Monitor workloads to ensure business goals are achieved
 * Assist in the processing of data, including matching and maintaining specific object data
 * Develop data standards and provide input to strategy for the solution
 * Assist in development of, and execution of, data quality programmes
 * Contribute to the development and implementation of improvements and best practice in processes and procedures
 * Contribute to relevant business and people planning, and develop local strategies to improve against key performance measures
 * Prepare correspondence such as reports, corporate and technical documentation for review by executive level staff
 * Resolve or escalate issues as required and suggest alternative approaches
 * Exercise appropriate delegation in accordance with legislation and guidelines
   
   

Technical skills


 * Experience in data analysis including data governance and data management in government/public sector or industry equivalent. 2. Experience in at least one of the following tools - Data Lake, HUE, SAS, SQL, Aged Care, EDW/Teradata, Mainframe, Tableau. 3. Working knowledge of Data Lake, Hadoop, EDW, Cloudera and Hue. 4. Experience in designing and delivering data analytics solutions for large and complex projects.
   
   

Mandatory Criteria


 * Business intelligence: Level 3 (SFIA)
   
   

Sources and prepares data for analysis and performs standard business intelligence analysis activities. Creates and delivers standard reports in accordance with stakeholder needs and conforming to agreed standards. Investigates the need for new or revised business intelligence analysis. Contributes to the recommendation of improvements. Engages with stakeholders under direction.


 * Business situation analysis: Level 5 (SFIA)
   
   

Plans, manages and investigates business situation analysis where there is significant ambiguity and complexity. Advises on the approach and techniques to be used for business situation analysis. Ensures holistic view adopted to identify and analyse wide-ranging problems and opportunities. Engages and collaborates with a wide range of stakeholders, including those at the management level. Gains agreement from stakeholders to conclusions and recommendations. Contributes to definition of organisational standards and guidelines for business situation analysis.


 * Data communication: Level 3 (DCF)
   
   

Can develop and deliver advanced level narrative to communicate insights drawn from complex data sources and outputs Maintains understanding of new trends and innovations relating to data communication (including Artificial Intelligence-based technologies) and develops skills in these where relevant Understands the importance of translating technical concepts into non-technical language, and can adapt communication effectively for a range of audiences. Can use innovative approaches to improve the process of summarising data into meaningful narratives Uses high quality analytics and visualisation to communicate insights from data Can effectively listen to technical and business stakeholders, and understand and interpret their data needs


 * Data management: Level 4 (SFIA)
   
   

Devises and implements master data management processes for specific subsets of data. Assesses the integrity of data from multiple sources. Provides advice on the transformation of data from one format/medium to another. Maintains and implements information handling procedures. Enables the availability, integrity and searchability of information through the application of formal data and metadata structures and protection measures.


 * Data modelling and design: Level 4 (SFIA)
   
   

Investigates enterprise data requirements where there is some complexity and ambiguity. Plans own data modelling and design activities, selecting appropriate techniques and the correct level of detail for meeting assigned objectives. Provides advice and guidance to others using the data structures and associated components.


 * Data outputs, products or services: Level 3 (DCF)
   
   

Has expert knowledge about the production of a data output, product or service Provides expertise in developing new products or data services to meet evolving requirements, needs and opportunities. Can build the capability of others in the delivery of data outputs, products or services


 * Data visualisation: Level 4 (SFIA)
   
   

Applies a variety of visualisation techniques and designs the content and appearance of data visuals. Operationalises and automates activities for efficient and timely production of data visuals. Selects appropriate visualisation approaches from a range of applicable options. Contributes to exploration and experimentation in data visualisation.


 * Database design: Level 3 (SFIA)
   
   

Interprets installation standards to meet project needs and produces database or data warehouse component specifications. Develops appropriate physical database or data warehouse design elements, within set policies, to meet data requirements.


 * Identify research questions: Level 3 (DCF)
   
   

Uses a range of techniques to assess data needs and identify gaps, towards the formulation of appropriate research questions


 * Integrate data: Level 2 (DCF)
   
   

Can perform data integration using standard tools and can implement quality controls Knows where to obtain expert advice on data integration as needed Is able to understand and amend existing code (programming language) to integrate data Can assess datasets' suitability for linkage and extract appropriately prepared datasets


 * Programming/software development: Level 3 (SFIA)
   
   

Designs, codes, verifies, tests, documents, amends and refactors moderately complex programs/scripts. Applies agreed standards and tools to achieve a well-engineered result. Monitors and reports on progress. Identifies issues related to software development activities. Proposes practical solutions to resolve issues. Collaborates in reviews of work with others as appropriate.


 * Statistical data analysis: Level 3 (DCF)
   
   

Contributes to the development of new functionality for statistical analysis applications, which enables new ways of doing things Can write custom scripts and code in a statistical computing language to conduct complex analytical tasks Maintains understanding of new trends and innovations relating to statistical data analysis (including Artificial Intelligence-based technologies) and develops skills in these where relevant


 * Subject matter expertise: Level 3 (DCF)
   
   

Is an expert resource on the subject matter area associated with data use, including understanding and influencing the effective use of the data within that subject matter area and the relationship between that use and other data use contexts

Salary Expectation

$75,000 - $85,000 p.a.

ABOUT THE ROLE: Due to continued growth, Warrikal are currently seeking a Data Analyst - Procurement to join our team on a permanent, full-time basis in West Perth.

Responsibilities

This new position will be focused on supporting our Procurement function and will work closely with our finance team. Your responsibilities will include:


 * Identify, evaluate, and select potential suppliers based on quality, reliability, and cost-effectiveness.
 * Assist in the implementation of cost saving initiatives and related processes.
 * Develop self-service tools and business intelligence software including PowerBI, SAP Factors and excel.
 * Collaborate with internal stakeholders to understand procurement needs and develop strategic procurement plans.
 * Conduct regular cost analysis and benchmarking to identify opportunities for cost reduction.
 * Ensure compliance with company policies, industry regulations, and ethical standards.
 * Identify and mitigate potential risks related to procurement activities.
 * Maintain accurate and organized procurement records, including contracts, purchase orders, and supplier information.
 * Generate regular reports on procurement activities, cost savings, and vendor performance.
 * Implement system improvement initiatives to optimise operational efficiency and align with contemporary practices.
 * Develop and contribute to the delivery of improvement initiatives which support business priorities for continuous improvement.
 * Identify, Investigate, and analyse business processes, procedures and work practices and make recommendations to align with the business strategic objective.
   
   
   

ABOUT YOU:


 * Bachelor or higher degree in Data Science, Data Analytics or other relevant discipline.
 * 5+ years’ experience in business improvement roles in supply chain or related fields would be considered in lieu of formal qualifications.
 * Prove experience using accounting software including Pronto, Microsoft power BI, SAP factors is desirable.
 * Strong negotiation and communication skills.
 * Familiarity with relevant laws, regulations, and industry standards.
 * Proficient in procurement software and Microsoft Office Suite.
 * Well-developed written and verbal communication skills.
 * Demonstrate an ability to work autonomously and collaboratively with colleagues across all business units.
 * Build and sustain positive relationships with all stakeholders, including Clients, vendors, and co-workers.
 * Proactively seek and accept guidance and feedback provided by subject matter experts.
 * Driven and determined to achieve objectives through continued professional development.
 * Good organisational and time management skills.
 * Personal qualities of integrity, credibility, and commitment.
 * Solid technical aptitude, analytical and problem-solving skills.
   
   
   

ABORIGINAL & TORRES STRAIT ISLANDERS ARE STRONGLY ENCOURAGED TO APPLY.

When you join Warrikal you will be joining a ‘family’; a workplace that is diverse, empowering, and supportive; a place where everyone is treated as equals with integrity and respect. We value strong and passionate team players who act with honesty, integrity and who inspire others to be their best. In return you will be part of an organisation that supports the careers of all employees and provides opportunities to develop into the leaders of tomorrow.

description:
Come and join a thriving company and become part of a diverse global collective of free-thinkers, entrepreneurs and industry experts who are all driven to use technology to reimagine what’s possible.  Capgemini. Get the future you want.
 
For more about why Capgemini https://www.capgemini.com/au-en/careers/why-join-capgemini/
 
Let’s talk about the roles and responsibilities
 
As a Data Analyst, you’ll be involved in designing and implementing strategies that enhance customer engagement through data insights. You’ll work across one-to-one, digital, and broadcast media channels, using advanced analytical techniques, marketing technologies, and advertising tools to achieve measurable results.
 
Key Responsibilities:


 * Analytics Leadership: Drive squads to implement evidence-based marketing strategies, using advanced data analytics and insights.
 * Pre-Campaign Analytics: Shape customer contact strategies and identify targeting opportunities through data-driven planning.
 * Post-Campaign Optimization: Analyze campaign performance to ensure continuous improvement and optimization.
 * Data-Driven Insights: Facilitate actionable insights to guide marketing activities and customer engagement opportunities.
 * Visualization & Storytelling: Present findings through compelling data visualizations and impactful presentations tailored to diverse audiences.
 * Innovative Frameworks: Develop improved analysis approaches and test-and-learn frameworks to refine marketing campaigns.
   
   

Qualifications:

 * Expertise in advanced data analytics, with experience driving marketing decisions through insights.
 * Strong knowledge of marketing technologies and advertising technology.
 * Proven ability to perform both pre- and post-campaign analytics.
 * Excellent communication skills, with the ability to present complex data in an engaging and actionable manner.
 * Collaborative mindset and the ability to work across diverse teams to implement data-driven strategies.
 * Passion for innovation and continuous improvement in analytics approaches.
   
   

About Capgemini
 
At Capgemini, we are more than just a business, we are a diverse global collective of strategic and technological experts who are passionate about finding ways technology can help our clients, our people and our communities get the future they want.
Our people are the key to making this vision a reality, which is why we have been recognised by the Australian Workplace Equality Index as LGTBQ+ ‘Employer of the Year’ and ‘Inclusion of Trans and Gender Diverse Employees’ for the past two years. We believe in creating a safe, flexible, and inclusive culture where everyone can bring their authentic selves to work, contributing to our inclusive culture and truly belong, and our staff-led community groups are a testament to this commitment. We are committed to being active allies for everyone.
We believe by combining the power of the latest technology with our human energy, we can drive sustainable thinking into our operations and the work we do with clients. Its why we are committing to being carbon neutral for our own operations no later than 2025 and across our supply chain by 2030 and committed to becoming a net zero business by 2040.
Empower yourself with the knowledge and skills you need to succeed with our access to premier learning platforms, sought-after certifications and boundless development opportunities. You’ll be encouraged to gain at least 40 hours of training each year.
 
For over 50 years our values and ethics have been at heart of our identity. From our approach to ethics to the way we interact with one another, honesty, boldness, trust, freedom, team spirit, modesty, and fun guide and inspire all we do and have led to us being recognised as one of the World’s Most Ethical Companies by the Ethisphere Institute 12 years in a row.
 
Our Commitment to Diversity & Inclusion
Don’t meet every single requirement for this role? Studies have shown women and people from diverse minority backgrounds are less likely to apply to jobs unless they meet every single requirement. At Capgemini, we are dedicated to building a diverse, inclusive, and authentic workplace, so if you’re excited about this role but your experience doesn’t align perfectly, we encourage you to apply and tell us what you can bring to the role.
We understand for some people, a standard hiring processes can come with challenges. If you are living with a disability, are gender diverse or neurodivergent and we can provide support with access requirements or by making an adjustment to our hiring process, please contact us at talentacquisitionaunz@capgemini.com
 
Information Security and Compliance
 
Capgemini Australia has developed and manages, process orientated Management Systems compliant to the requirements of ISO9001, ISO27001 and ISO14001. We are committed to delivering secure solutions and services through state-of-the-art processes and continual improvement frameworks in line with industry best practices as well as contractual, statutory, and regulatory requirements.

Agoda is an online travel booking platform for accommodations, flights, and more. We build and deploy cutting-edge technology that connects travelers with a global network of 4.7M hotels and holiday properties worldwide, plus flights, activities, and more . Based in Asia and part of Booking Holdings, our 7,100+ employees representing 95+ nationalities in 27 markets foster a work environment rich in diversity, creativity, and collaboration. We innovate through a culture of experimentation and ownership,?enhancing the ability for our customers to experience the world.

Our Purpose – Bridging the World Through Travel

We believe travel allows people to enjoy, learn and experience more of the amazing world we live in. It brings individuals and cultures closer together, fostering empathy, understanding and happiness.

This department is highly data-driven and focused on developing at-scale marketing programs that improve the lifetime value of Agoda customers through measurable marketing programs and channels. The team is a blend of the best analysts, marketing strategists, and data scientists in the world. The marketing leadership at Agoda have deep experience in data science, product, strategy, and other marketing fields and have built an organization that thrives on data, creative ideas, and technology. Nuage is partnering with a leading consultancy to find a highly skilled AI/ML Engineer to join their team on a permanent basis. This is an exciting opportunity to work on innovative AI projects, leveraging cutting-edge machine learning technologies to drive impactful solutions.




Key Responsibilities:

 * Design, develop, and deploy machine learning models using frameworks such as TensorFlow, PyTorch, and Scikit-learn.
 * Build and maintain end-to-end machine learning pipelines, including data preprocessing, model training, evaluation, and deployment.
 * Integrate large language models and generative AI tools using frameworks like LangChain.
 * Optimize model performance and scalability in cloud environments such as AWS, Azure, or GCP.
 * Collaborate with cross-functional teams, including data scientists, engineers, and business stakeholders, to understand requirements and deliver AI solutions.
 * Implement best practices for version control, reproducibility, and CI/CD for machine learning workflows.
 * Research and experiment with emerging AI techniques to stay ahead of industry trends.
 * Monitor and troubleshoot issues in deployed AI systems to ensure reliability and accuracy.




Key Skills and Experience:

 * Proven experience as an AI/ML Engineer or in a similar role.
 * Proficiency in Python and machine learning libraries/frameworks (e.g., TensorFlow, PyTorch, Scikit-learn).
 * Experience with large language models (e.g., GPT, BERT) and generative AI technologies.
 * Familiarity with LangChain or similar frameworks for LLM application development.
 * Strong knowledge of cloud platforms and services (AWS, Azure, GCP) for AI/ML workloads.
 * Solid understanding of MLOps practices, including model deployment and monitoring.
 * Expertise in data engineering concepts, including feature engineering and data pipelines.

 * Strong problem-solving skills and ability to work in a collaborative team environment.

What’s On Offer:

 * Competitive salary and benefits package.
 * Opportunity to work on cutting-edge AI and machine learning projects.
 * Career development and learning opportunities.
 * Collaborative and innovative work environment.
 * Hybrid work arrangements

description:
At CoreLogic, we are driven by a single mission—to make the property industry faster, smarter, and more people-centric. CoreLogic is the trusted source for property intelligence, with unmatched precision, depth, breadth, and insights across the entire ecosystem. Our talented team of 5,000 employees globally uses our network, scale, connectivity and technology to drive the largest asset class in the world. Join us as we work toward our vision of fueling a thriving global property ecosystem and a more resilient society.

CoreLogic is committed to cultivating a diverse and inclusive work culture that inspires innovation and bold thinking; it's a place where you can collaborate, feel valued, develop skills and directly impact the real estate economy. We know our people are our greatest asset. At CoreLogic, you can be yourself, lift people up and make an impact. By putting clients first and continuously innovating, we're working together to set the pace for unlocking new possibilities that better serve the property industry.

Job Description:

What is the role?

We are seeking a highly skilled and motivated Quantitative Analyst with a passion for property to join our dynamic team. The ideal candidate will have a strong analytical background and experience producing actionable insights and developing machine learning models in real estate analytics. This role will be pivotal in driving the development and enhancement of our analytics products and solutions, providing critical insights to support strategic decision-making within the company

What will you be doing?

Data analysis and modelling:


 * Design, develop and implement methods to analyse real estate data and market trends.
 * Utilise statistical and machine learning techniques to develop and continuously develop existing analytics products.
   
   
   

Product, research and insights:


 * Collaborate with cross-functional teams, including data and machine learning engineers, products managers and the research team, to identify opportunities for leveraging analytics in decision-making and business operations
 * Conduct in-depth research on property market trends and economic indicators to inform model development and product enhancements.
 * Stay current with industry advancements, emerging technologies and best practices in quantitative analysis, machine learning and GenerativeAI.
 * Present research findings, model output and product updates to senior management and clients, effectively communicating complex concepts clearly and concisely.
   
   
   

Job Qualifications:

Are you the right fit ?

To be successful in this role the key competencies required include:


 * Bachelor’s or Master’s degree in a quantitative field such as Mathematics, Statistics, Computer Science or a related discipline.
 * 3+ years experience in a quantitative analysis role, proven track record of producing actionable insights to inform business decision-making.
 * Previous experience in spatial analytics, including working with geographic information systems (GIS) and spatial data analysis techniques
 * Proficiency in programming R. Additional experience with python is a bonus.
 * Previous experience working with cloud platform such as AWS, GCP or Azure, including cloud-based data storage, processing and model deployment.
 * Strong analytical and problem-solving skills with the ability to think critically and make data-driven decisions.
 * Excellent communication and presentation skills, with the ability to convey complex technical information to non-technical stakeholders.
   
   
   

Why join CoreLogic?

CoreLogic is the leading provider of property data and analytics in Australia and New Zealand. We’re fiercely independent, and we’re considered the best in the business. Every day, our data scientists and researchers collect data from over 4.5 billion points across the CoreLogic universe. We then rinse and finesse this data to transform it into powerful property market insights that drive the best property decisions.

CoreLogic's Diversity Commitment:

CoreLogic is fully committed to employing a diverse workforce and creating an inclusive work environment that embraces everyone’s unique contributions, experiences and values. We offer an empowered work environment that encourages creativity, initiative and professional growth and provides a competitive salary and benefits package. We are better together when we support and recognize our differences.

Equal Opportunity Employer Statement:

CoreLogic is an Equal Opportunity employer committed to attracting and retaining the best-qualified people available, without regard to race, colour, gender, sexual orientation, age, physical or mental disability, marital status, family or carer’s responsibilities, pregnancy, religion, political opinion, national extraction (place of birth or ancestry), social origin (class, caste or socio-occupational category), industrial activities (such as belonging to a trade union). CoreLogic maintains a Drug-Free Workplace.

Please apply on our website for consideration.

Privacy Policy - http://www.corelogic.com/privacy.aspx

By providing your telephone number, you agree to receive automated (SMS) text messages at that number from CoreLogic regarding all matters related to your application and, if you are hired, your employment and company business. Message & data rates may apply. You can opt out at any time by responding STOP or UNSUBSCRIBING and will automatically be opted out company-wide.

description:
HCM Program Data Analyst

Parramatta/Eveleigh
12 Months Contract

Talent International is working in partnership with a large government organisation to assist in sourcing an experienced 'HCM Program Data Analyst'.

Key Responsibilities:

 * Support the development of the Data Management and Migration Strategies and associated Data Architecture, ensuring compliance with industry standards and best practices
 * Support the development of data migration designs and plans
 * Assist with the creation and maintenance of the program's data reconciliation framework
 * Interact with subject matter experts and internal department stakeholders to understand and document legacy data requirements
 * Contribute to data profiling activities and provide guidance to service and support units around source data cleansing activities
 * Engage with the Functional stream and solution implementation partner to understand target state solution design
 * Create and maintain source to target data mappings while being a point of contact for relevant data migration activities
 * Collaborate with the data migration partner in undertaking extraction, transformation and load (ETL) tasks
 * Assist with and contribute to data migration runs and related activities
 * Conduct ongoing data reconciliation activities to review, validate and report on the comprehensiveness and quality of data migration runs
 * Identify and assist in the resolution of data migration defects, particularly when these relate to data verification issues
 * Work closely with external partners / experts to build an internal knowledge base and expertise for operational hand-over.
 * Develop and maintain effective relationships across the program and ITD stakeholders and provide guidance to stakeholders in relation to business improvements relating to data (e.g. governance).
 * Provide production support, troubleshooting, and resolving data issues in a timely manner to reduce downtime

Key Criteria:

 * 5+ years data analysis and migration experience in large organisations
 * 3+ years of data migration experience with HR data sets within HCM systems
 * 3+ years of data migration experience with SAP SuccessFactors and/or SAP ERP Central Component (ECC).
 * High attention to detail and strong documentation and stakeholder skills
 * Strong analytical skills with the ability to work with large datasets and draw insights based on the underlying data.
 * Proficiency with SQL (desirable).

description:
Data Analyst ( Level 2)

Location: Perth, Western Australia

Apply now

ROSEN Asia Pacific is recruiting a Data Analyst (Level 2 ) to join its Evaluation Department in based in Perth, Australia.

In this role you will be responsible efficiently analyze inspection data as well as merge, compare, validate, and report analysis results in accordance with the project requirements. In addition, the role shall also be responsible for the additional functions of Data Evaluation Reporting and Data Evaluation Processing (as required) and at the direction of the Head of Evaluation (AP) and Work Lead (OCE)

What you can expect Responsible for


 * Gathering all required and available data from Evaluation Coordinator and Data Processor
 * Analyzing contractually requested inspection data
 * Correlation and comparison of individual analysis results of different inspections
 * Merging of correlated and compared analysis results for combined reporting
 * Validating of data analysis results considering result’s plausibility, reporting specifications and (if available) in-field measurements
 * Configuration and preparation of software handed out to client
 * Reporting of data analysis results in accordance with project reporting requirements
 * Completion and review of preliminary and final survey report in accordance with project requirements
 * Review of all requested deliveries (reports, software) in accordance with project requirements
   
   

What you will bring


 * Minimum Certification Level 2 in main technology (Corporate written Practice Qualification and certification of ILI personnel)
